1
00:00:30,263 --> 00:00:33,164
<i>[ Crickets Chirping ]</i>

2
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:22,080
<i>[ Man's Voice ]</i>
<i>Yes.</i>

3
00:01:22,182 --> 00:01:24,082
[ Grunting ]

4
00:01:57,517 --> 00:01:59,417
<i>Yes.</i>

5
00:02:22,075 --> 00:02:23,975
<i>Yes.</i>

6
00:02:45,131 --> 00:02:47,065
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Please. Please.</i>
<i>Don't worry. Don't worry.</i>

7
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:49,931
It's utter chaos
around here.

8
00:02:50,036 --> 00:02:52,630
And I'm terrified
that we're running
out of time.

9
00:02:52,739 --> 00:02:54,639
Am I trying to be
too perfect ?

10
00:02:54,741 --> 00:02:56,971
Oh, but I want it to be
so exquisite.
So do we.

11
00:02:57,076 --> 00:03:01,536
But we're trying to be
too exquisite.
Why not aim for the stars ?

12
00:03:01,648 --> 00:03:03,548
Good morning.
Good morning.

13
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:06,983
We do need some answers
on the flowers.
Ah, yes, freesia, freesia.

14
00:03:07,086 --> 00:03:10,078
Everywhere freesia.
Daddy loves freesia.

15
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:13,250
Good morning. Good morning.
Oh. Hello. Hi.

16
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:15,259
<i>Lights ?</i>
''Lights.''

17
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:19,354
Not too bright
and not too dark.
[ Chuckles ]

18
00:03:19,465 --> 00:03:22,332
I'm looking for
a saffron glow,

19
00:03:22,435 --> 00:03:24,665
sort of tea-dance '20s.

20
00:03:24,771 --> 00:03:26,898
If food is the prose
of a party,

21
00:03:27,006 --> 00:03:30,203
then lights
are its poetry.

22
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:36,806
It works.
If food is the prose of
a party, lights are its poetry.

23
00:03:36,916 --> 00:03:41,250
I like that. If music were
the food of love, play on.
I'm going out of my mind.

24
00:03:41,354 --> 00:03:43,254
Good morning,
Mr. Parrish.

25
00:03:43,356 --> 00:03:46,018
What do you think
of all this, Helen ?
It's gonna be beautiful.

26
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:48,525
And Allison says
the president may come.

27
00:03:48,628 --> 00:03:52,291
The president's got better
things to do than come to my
birthday party.
<i>Like what ?</i>

28
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:54,525
Daddy ?
Do you have a minute ?
Good morning, Allison.

29
00:03:54,634 --> 00:03:56,795
Not much more.
Big day in the big city.

30
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:59,303
What's on your mind ?
Fireworks.
Update:

31
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:02,203
We are constructing
the number 65 on the barge.
Mm-hmm.

32
00:04:02,308 --> 00:04:06,142
Archers from the State College
of New Paltz will shoot
flaming arrows at it.

33
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:10,649
When it catches fire,
it will give us the effect
of a Viking funeral,

34
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,650
but with none
of the morbidity.

35
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:15,812
The Hudson River Authority
says that for you, they'll make
a special dispensation.

36
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:18,720
But, of course,
there will be
an overtime bill...

37
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:20,725
for the Poughkeepsie
Fire Department.

38
00:04:20,827 --> 00:04:24,160
So, what
do you think ?

39
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:26,630
Good ?
No good ?
[ Chuckles ]

40
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:29,896
Allison, I trust you.
This is your thing.

41
00:04:30,003 --> 00:04:33,939
But it's your birthday.
I hate arrows.
They make me nervous.

42
00:04:35,074 --> 00:04:37,440
Good morning, Dad.
Good morning, honey.

43
00:04:37,543 --> 00:04:39,875
Morning.
Morning. You're ''Honey.''
I'm ''Allison.''

44
00:04:39,979 --> 00:04:42,140
[ Chuckling ]
Oh.

45
00:04:42,248 --> 00:04:46,514
Oh, Dad, Drew called from
the helicopter, and they're
still two minutes away.

46
00:04:46,619 --> 00:04:48,746
Drew's aboard ?
Mm-hmm.

47
00:04:48,855 --> 00:04:50,823
He wanted to ride
back down with you.

48
00:04:50,923 --> 00:04:55,019
So why don't you sit down,
relax, and get some food
in that flat tummy of yours.

49
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:57,028
Are you coming ?
No.

50
00:04:57,130 --> 00:05:00,327
You've got patients
to attend to. I've got
three hysterical chefs,

51
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:02,458
one of whom loves truffles,
the other one hates truffles,

52
00:05:02,568 --> 00:05:04,934
and the third one
doesn't even know
what truffles are.

53
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:07,700
I hate parties.
But, Daddy,
calm down.

54
00:05:07,807 --> 00:05:10,002
You're gonna love it.
I swear.

55
00:05:10,109 --> 00:05:13,340
Isn't it enough to be on
the Earth for 65 years without
having to be reminded of it ?

56
00:05:13,446 --> 00:05:16,677
- No.
- [ Chuckling ]

57
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:22,015
Will you relax ?
I know it's a big deal day.

58
00:05:22,121 --> 00:05:25,420
How'd you know that ?
Drew told me.

59
00:05:25,525 --> 00:05:27,425
Does he tell you
everything ?

60
00:05:27,527 --> 00:05:30,052
I hope so.

61
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:32,461
You like him,
don't you ?

62
00:05:32,565 --> 00:05:35,295
Yep,
I guess so.

63
00:05:35,401 --> 00:05:37,892
I don't want
to interfere, but, uh--
Then don't.

64
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:40,302
<i>[ Helicopter Approaching ]</i>

65
00:05:40,406 --> 00:05:42,897
<i>Well, here comes</i>
<i>our boy now.</i>

66
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:44,909
Shall we ?

67
00:05:46,245 --> 00:05:48,645
- Okay.
- Hello, beautiful.

68
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:51,749
Hi.

69
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,851
Good morning, Drew.
Thanks for coming up.

70
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:02,655
Well, big day.
Wanted to line up
a few ducks before kickoff.

71
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:05,560
Any thoughts,
last minute refinements,
variations, anything ?

72
00:06:05,665 --> 00:06:09,863
Thoughts, no.
I did hear a voice
last night.

73
00:06:09,969 --> 00:06:12,028
A voice ?
In my sleep.

74
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:14,572
What'd it say ?
''Yes.''

75
00:06:14,674 --> 00:06:18,405
[ Chuckles ]
Yes to the deal ?
Maybe. Who knows ?

76
00:06:18,511 --> 00:06:20,411
You know how voices are.

77
00:06:20,513 --> 00:06:23,710
Hmm ?
I thank you, Delia.

78
00:06:23,816 --> 00:06:26,011
Okay, let's go.
Delia, your pen.

79
00:06:27,253 --> 00:06:29,380
<i>Hi, Bill.</i>
<i>How you doin' ?</i>
Morning, Quince.

80
00:06:29,489 --> 00:06:32,049
I'm doin' great,
and you ?
Oh, I'm great.

81
00:06:32,158 --> 00:06:34,649
This is it, ''B-day.''
Huh ?
Sorry.

82
00:06:34,761 --> 00:06:38,561
Bontecou day.
We're gonna close...
with Big John.

83
00:06:38,664 --> 00:06:40,598
Look at you, Bill.
You're all cool as a cat.

84
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:43,965
Over at Bontecou's,
I'll bet he's just
shittin' in his pants.

85
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:47,801
Remember, everybody,
big meeting tonight
at Daddy's.

86
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:51,570
Dinner.
You, too, Drew.
We have lots of loose ends.

87
00:06:51,677 --> 00:06:55,204
Not my birthday again ?
You're only 65 once,
Dad.

88
00:06:55,314 --> 00:06:57,214
Thank God.
Now let's get
the day started.

89
00:06:57,316 --> 00:06:59,876
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Remember, dinner in the city</i>
<i>at Daddy's!</i>

90
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:15,462
Mm-hmm.
It's so ridiculous.

91
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:17,559
Do you love Drew ?
<i>[ Drew On Telephone,</i>
<i>Indistinct ]</i>

92
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:20,935
<i>[ Drew ]</i>
<i>No, don't do anything.</i>
<i>Just stay exactly where--</i>

93
00:07:22,508 --> 00:07:26,808
Do you love Drew ?
<i>He's not gonna get</i>
<i>a better offer than that.</i>

94
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:31,907
[ Sighs ]
You mean, like you loved Mom ?
Forget about me and Mom.

95
00:07:33,853 --> 00:07:38,517
- Are you gonna marry him ?
- <i>[ Drew ]</i>
<i>Oh, come on.</i>

96
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,525
I'm probably.

97
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:44,460
Listen, I'm crazy about
the guy. He's smart.
He's aggressive.

98
00:07:44,564 --> 00:07:49,524
<i>He could carry Parrish</i>
<i>Communications into the 2 1 st</i>
<i>century and me along with it.</i>

99
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,536
Mm-hmm.
So, what's wrong with that ?

100
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:55,004
That's for me.
I'm talking about you.

101
00:07:56,576 --> 00:07:59,511
<i>It's not what you say about</i>
<i>Drew. It's what you don't say.</i>

102
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:02,477
Maybe you're not listening.

103
00:08:02,582 --> 00:08:04,482
Oh, yes, I am.

104
00:08:04,584 --> 00:08:06,552
<i>[ Drew ]</i>
<i>Give him whatever he wants.</i>

105
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:11,453
There's not an ounce
of excitement, not a...
whisper of a thrill.

106
00:08:11,557 --> 00:08:15,391
And this relationship
has all the passion
of a pair of titmice.

107
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,827
<i>I want you to get</i>
<i>swept away out there.</i>

108
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:20,763
I want you to levitate.
I want you to...

109
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:23,233
sing with rapture
and dance like a dervish.

110
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:26,066
- Oh, that's all.
- Yeah. Be deliriously happy,

111
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:28,504
or at least
leave yourself open to be.

112
00:08:29,742 --> 00:08:32,267
Okay.
[ Sighs ]

113
00:08:32,378 --> 00:08:34,869
''Be deliriously happy.''
I shall, uh--

114
00:08:34,981 --> 00:08:37,142
I shall do my utmost.

115
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,775
[ Chuckling ]

116
00:08:40,887 --> 00:08:43,378
I know it's
a cornball thing.

117
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:47,084
But love is passion,

118
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:49,093
obsession,

119
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:51,891
someone
you can't live without.

120
00:08:51,998 --> 00:08:54,762
<i>I say,</i>
<i>fall head over heels.</i>

121
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:59,566
Find someone you can love
like crazy and who will
love you the same way back.

122
00:08:59,672 --> 00:09:04,575
How do you find him ?
Well, you forget your head,
and you listen to your heart.

123
00:09:04,677 --> 00:09:06,577
And I'm not hearing
any heart.

124
00:09:06,679 --> 00:09:11,514
<i>'Cause the truth is, honey,</i>
<i>there's no sense living</i>
<i>your life without this.</i>

125
00:09:11,617 --> 00:09:15,849
To make the journey
and not fall deeply in love,

126
00:09:15,955 --> 00:09:19,049
well, you haven't lived
a life at all.

127
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:25,356
<i>But you have to try,</i>
<i>'cause if you haven't tried,</i>
<i>you haven't lived.</i>

128
00:09:26,465 --> 00:09:29,059
Bravo !

129
00:09:29,168 --> 00:09:31,102
Oh, you're tough.

130
00:09:31,203 --> 00:09:33,899
[ Sighs ]

131
00:09:34,006 --> 00:09:36,668
I'm sorry.
Okay.

132
00:09:36,776 --> 00:09:39,904
Give it to me again,
but the short version
this time.

133
00:09:40,012 --> 00:09:42,776
Okay.
Stay open.

134
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:46,079
Who knows ?
Lightning could strike.

135
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:51,751
- [ Chuckling ]
- Yeah ?

136
00:09:51,857 --> 00:09:53,757
Yeah.

137
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:06,133
<i>What do you think ?</i>
<i>Is it just the executive</i>
<i>committee,</i>

138
00:10:06,238 --> 00:10:08,206
or are you guys
gonna use me ?

139
00:10:08,307 --> 00:10:11,333
Quince, man, thanks for
the offer, but it's all set
for just me and Bill.

140
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:16,211
More people might--
I know. I know,
gum up the works.

141
00:10:16,315 --> 00:10:18,875
[ Bill's Voice ]
''I want you
to get swept away.''

142
00:10:18,985 --> 00:10:21,647
Huh ?
I was just sayin' to Quince
that we won't need him until--

143
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:23,688
Did you hear something ?
Yeah, but I was
just sayin' to Quince--

144
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:26,155
No, no, no.
Not you.
What's the matter, Daddy ?

145
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:32,489
Nothing. I'm sorry.
[ Bill's Voice ]
''I want you to levitate.

146
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:36,034
I want you to sing with rapture
and dance like a dervish.''

147
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:40,397
''Dance like a dervish'' ?
Daddy, what is it ?

148
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:44,933
Nothing, I'm just
talking to myself.
You know me.

149
00:10:45,044 --> 00:10:47,478
No, I've never known you
to talk to yourself.

150
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:50,708
Oh, well,
can I give you a lift ?

151
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:54,377
No, I'm gonna catch a cab.
Listen, are you okay ?
Yeah.

152
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:57,479
Got my garters on,
my ears pricked--
ready for action.

153
00:10:57,590 --> 00:10:59,558
Okay. Well--
Go get 'em, Pops.

154
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:02,059
You're damn right.
Okay.

155
00:11:03,162 --> 00:11:04,686
<i>[ Car Door Closes ]</i>

156
00:11:05,364 --> 00:11:08,856
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.</i>
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

157
00:11:08,968 --> 00:11:10,868
<i>Oh, haven't heard</i>
<i>that one before.</i>

158
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:13,734
<i>I'm sorry.</i>
<i>I had to say it.</i>

159
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:16,774
<i>Honey ? Honey ?</i>
Hi, George.

160
00:11:16,876 --> 00:11:20,607
[ Chuckling ]
Honey, you have to go on.

161
00:11:20,713 --> 00:11:22,908
Okay ?
There's a time to sow
and a time to reap.

162
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:25,210
You have to sow.
[ Clattering ]

163
00:11:25,317 --> 00:11:27,683
<i>Sorry.</i>
<i>Excuse me.</i>

164
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:29,687
No, I liked him.
I don't like him anymore.

165
00:11:29,789 --> 00:11:32,019
<i>'Cause you're my honey.</i>

166
00:11:32,124 --> 00:11:34,092
Someone messes with you,
they mess with me.

167
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:37,594
That's it. I'm on a plane
in a heartbeat.
You let me know.

168
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:41,724
Yep, when I get my phone in,
you're my first call.
I promise.

169
00:11:41,834 --> 00:11:44,860
Hit the books, get the degree.
One day we'll be hanging out
a shingle together.

170
00:11:44,970 --> 00:11:47,063
How's that ?
Mmm ? Okay.

171
00:11:47,173 --> 00:11:50,336
You all right ?
[ Laughing ]
Yes.

172
00:11:50,443 --> 00:11:53,003
<i>You bet.</i>
<i>Be strong.</i>

173
00:11:53,112 --> 00:11:55,273
<i>I love you.</i>
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

174
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:13,898
Morning.
Good morning.

175
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,900
[ Sighs ]

176
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:20,270
I was talkin'
kind of loud there.
I'm sorry.

177
00:12:20,372 --> 00:12:23,273
Oh, not at all.

178
00:12:24,376 --> 00:12:26,571
It was fascinating.

179
00:12:28,047 --> 00:12:29,947
Yeah, what was fascinating
about it ?

180
00:12:30,049 --> 00:12:32,882
Um--
You and, uh, ''honey'' ?

181
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:38,781
It's my kid sister.
Oh.

182
00:12:40,326 --> 00:12:42,226
And she just broke up
with her boyfriend
and was thinking...

183
00:12:42,328 --> 00:12:44,558
about dropping out
of law school.

184
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:48,224
Oh, I'm sorry.
No, nothing to be
sorry about.

185
00:12:48,334 --> 00:12:52,395
That's the way it is with
men and women, isn't it ?
What's the way ?

186
00:12:52,505 --> 00:12:54,473
Nothing lasts.

187
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:56,666
Oh. Yeah, I agree.

188
00:12:56,776 --> 00:12:58,903
Really ? Why ?

189
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:03,638
No, I'm interested.

190
00:13:05,551 --> 00:13:07,451
I was just trying
to be agreeable.

191
00:13:09,555 --> 00:13:13,116
- [ Laughing ]
- Okay. All right.
I was sharpshooting.

192
00:13:13,225 --> 00:13:16,661
Oh.
<i>No, just that</i>
<i>''nothing lasts''stuff.</i>

193
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:19,094
<i>That was the problem with</i>
<i>Honey's guy. He didn't</i>
<i>know what he wanted.</i>

194
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:22,292
So, he's fooling around,
and she catches him at it.

195
00:13:22,401 --> 00:13:24,392
You know,
like one girlfriend
isn't enough for him.

196
00:13:26,739 --> 00:13:30,004
- So, you're a one-girl guy.
- Yes, I am.

197
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:33,610
<i>That's right.</i>
Right.

198
00:13:35,047 --> 00:13:36,947
Looking for her
right now, actually.

199
00:13:37,049 --> 00:13:39,984
<i>Mmm. Who knows ?</i>
<i>You might be her.</i>

200
00:13:40,119 --> 00:13:42,349
<i>No, don't laugh.</i>
<i>I just got into town.</i>

201
00:13:42,454 --> 00:13:44,581
I got the new job.

202
00:13:44,690 --> 00:13:46,885
I'm trying to get
into this apartment.

203
00:13:50,763 --> 00:13:53,061
Anyway,
so you're a doctor.

204
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:55,065
Mmm.
How'd you know ?

205
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:57,635
'Cause everyone's
a doctor around here.

206
00:13:57,770 --> 00:14:02,833
This apartment building--
Everyone's in green slippers,
the green pajamas.

207
00:14:02,942 --> 00:14:04,842
The guy I'm waiting for
to vacate--

208
00:14:04,944 --> 00:14:07,174
doctor.
He's a doctor.
[ Chuckling ]

209
00:14:07,279 --> 00:14:10,077
What kind of doctor ?

210
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:12,207
I'm a resident--
internal medicine.

211
00:14:13,752 --> 00:14:15,652
So, if I needed a doctor,
you could be it.

212
00:14:15,754 --> 00:14:17,984
I could be her.
Yeah.

213
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:20,024
You could be...
her.

214
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:22,059
Uh-huh.

215
00:14:23,462 --> 00:14:25,589
Yeah, I could.

216
00:14:28,601 --> 00:14:32,128
I'm-I'm working
at the hospital, so--
<i>I see.</i>

217
00:14:32,271 --> 00:14:35,172
<i>This is my lucky day.</i>
<i>I just get in</i>
<i>the big, bad city,</i>

218
00:14:35,274 --> 00:14:37,606
not only do I find a doctor,
but a beautiful woman, as well.

219
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:44,782
Do you mind me saying that ?

220
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,250
Oh-- No, of course.
No, it's fine.

221
00:14:47,353 --> 00:14:49,253
It's fine.
It's just--

222
00:14:49,355 --> 00:14:51,880
[ Chuckling ]
Listen, could I
buy you a cup of coffee ?

223
00:14:54,193 --> 00:14:58,061
I have some patients coming in,
so I should probably...
<i>Yeah, yeah.</i>

224
00:14:58,163 --> 00:15:00,723
<i>get goin'.</i>
I gotta get to the apartment
and get off to work.

225
00:15:00,866 --> 00:15:02,697
<i>Yeah.</i>
But I'd still like to have
another cup of coffee.

226
00:15:04,637 --> 00:15:06,935
- Um--
- Would you let me do that ?

227
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:11,567
- Well, yeah, okay.
- Deal.

228
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,978
Mmm.

229
00:15:38,404 --> 00:15:40,702
Good morning,
Mr. Parrish.
Morning,Jennifer.

230
00:15:40,806 --> 00:15:42,706
So, board convenes tomorrow.

231
00:15:42,808 --> 00:15:44,901
You'll recommend we close,
and it's a deal, right ?

232
00:15:46,578 --> 00:15:49,103
As close as a deal
could be.

233
00:15:49,248 --> 00:15:51,148
Olympic.

234
00:16:03,595 --> 00:16:06,496
[ Sighs ]

235
00:16:08,867 --> 00:16:11,301
[ Groaning ]

236
00:16:11,437 --> 00:16:14,270
[ Groaning ]
[ Bill's Voice ]
Yes.

237
00:16:14,373 --> 00:16:17,274
[ Panting ]

238
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:22,671
[ Groaning ]

239
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,620
Yes.

240
00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:32,054
[ Panting ]

241
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:35,456
''Yes'' what ?
Yes is the answer
to your question.

242
00:16:35,561 --> 00:16:37,461
Ah.

243
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:42,532
I didn't ask any question.

244
00:16:42,634 --> 00:16:44,534
I believe you did.

245
00:16:45,637 --> 00:16:48,834
[ Wheezing ]
Who are you ?

246
00:16:50,275 --> 00:16:54,302
Goddamn it.
What's going on here ?
I think you know.

247
00:16:54,446 --> 00:16:57,142
I don't.
Try.

248
00:16:58,751 --> 00:17:02,380
'''Cause if you haven't tried,
you haven't lived.''

249
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:08,358
What are you talking about ?

250
00:17:08,460 --> 00:17:10,360
What you were talking about.

251
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:15,098
Who is this guy ?

252
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:20,504
Tell me who you are.
Are you giving me orders ?

253
00:17:20,606 --> 00:17:24,201
- No. I'm sorry, I--
- No, you're not.

254
00:17:24,343 --> 00:17:26,811
You're trying
to <i>handle</i> the situation.

255
00:17:26,945 --> 00:17:32,349
But this is the one situation
you knew you never could handle.

256
00:17:32,484 --> 00:17:35,385
[ Groaning ]

257
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:40,791
It's enough...

258
00:17:42,694 --> 00:17:44,594
now.

259
00:17:46,865 --> 00:17:49,766
[ Panting ]

260
00:17:57,876 --> 00:17:59,776
Huh ?

261
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:06,017
Talk to me, please.

262
00:18:07,186 --> 00:18:09,780
There's gonna be
plenty of time for that.

263
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:13,323
What do you mean ?

264
00:18:15,828 --> 00:18:18,991
I think you know, Bill.

265
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:29,540
It's kind of
a pro bono job.

266
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:31,609
''Pro bono'' ?
Yeah.
[ Chuckling ]

267
00:18:31,743 --> 00:18:33,938
Meaning, doing good ?
That's me.

268
00:18:34,079 --> 00:18:35,979
Gonna be doing good
all your life ?

269
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:42,387
I know what you're saying.
It doesn't pay so well,
but, I like it.
Mm-hmm.

270
00:18:42,521 --> 00:18:46,719
<i>Eventually it'll depend</i>
<i>on the woman I marry, I think.</i>

271
00:18:46,859 --> 00:18:50,852
Maybe she'll want lots of kids,
a bigger house, better car, uh--

272
00:18:50,996 --> 00:18:53,487
College doesn't come cheap.
You know ? I don't know.

273
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:58,763
Wow.
Give up what you want
for the woman you marry.

274
00:18:58,904 --> 00:19:00,804
<i>Hmm.</i>

275
00:19:00,906 --> 00:19:03,136
Yeah, you know what ?
I would.

276
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:05,209
Yeah ?
<i>Gladly.</i>

277
00:19:06,578 --> 00:19:09,445
'Cause you make your choices,
you know ?

278
00:19:09,581 --> 00:19:13,108
Say, you and I,
if we were married, I would--
No, for an example, okay ?

279
00:19:13,252 --> 00:19:15,686
If you and I were married,
I would want to give you
what you need.

280
00:19:15,821 --> 00:19:18,949
That's all.
I'm talking about taking care
of each other the best you can.

281
00:19:19,091 --> 00:19:21,855
What's wrong with
taking care of a woman ?
She takes care of you.

282
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:24,986
You'll have a hard time
finding a woman like that
these days.

283
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:27,997
- Shoot, you think so ?
- Mm-hmm.

284
00:19:29,134 --> 00:19:32,365
I don't know.
Lightning could strike.

285
00:19:42,247 --> 00:19:44,238
I've gotta go.

286
00:19:44,383 --> 00:19:48,012
Yeah. Listen, did I say
something wrong ?
No ?
No.

287
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:50,953
No. No.
It was--
Sure ?

288
00:19:51,089 --> 00:19:53,887
It was so right,
it scares me.
That's all.

289
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,891
Just--

290
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,230
You know, I was thinking,
I don't want you
to be my doctor.

291
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:05,133
I don't want you to...
examine me and--

292
00:20:05,237 --> 00:20:07,501
Why ?

293
00:20:09,174 --> 00:20:11,074
Because I like you
so much.

294
00:20:14,813 --> 00:20:16,713
[ Chuckles ]

295
00:20:20,752 --> 00:20:24,347
And I-- I don't want
to examine you.

296
00:20:24,456 --> 00:20:27,983
You don't ?
Why not ?

297
00:20:28,093 --> 00:20:31,654
Because I like you
so much.
[ Both Laughing ]

298
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:37,129
Oh, boy.
Okay.

299
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:40,205
Now I gotta go, so--

300
00:20:40,305 --> 00:20:43,103
Yep, understood.
All right. All right.

301
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:45,540
Fair enough.
See ya.

302
00:20:45,644 --> 00:20:48,112
Bye. Bye.
Bye-bye.

303
00:21:56,782 --> 00:21:58,682
<i>[ Car Horn Blaring ]</i>

304
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:03,218
<i>[ Brakes Screeching ]</i>

305
00:22:28,313 --> 00:22:30,543
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Music.</i>

306
00:22:30,649 --> 00:22:34,176
<i>I know how you love music,</i>
<i>Daddy. And I want to have</i>
<i>music that pleases you,</i>

307
00:22:34,286 --> 00:22:37,847
but doesn't put a thousand
other people to sleep.

308
00:22:37,956 --> 00:22:42,393
I've agonized over it
and finally settled
on Sidney Brown.
Good.

309
00:22:42,494 --> 00:22:46,225
Twenty-four men--
very eclectic.
Mm-hmm.

310
00:22:46,331 --> 00:22:50,392
Plus, I'm feathering in
a Latin sextet on their breaks.

311
00:22:53,638 --> 00:22:56,505
You haven't heard
a word I've said, have you ?

312
00:22:58,944 --> 00:23:01,469
What, honey ? Sorry.
Daddy.

313
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:03,480
[ Bill's Voice ]
Yes.

314
00:23:04,783 --> 00:23:06,683
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Daddy ?</i>

315
00:23:06,785 --> 00:23:09,549
[ Sighs ]
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>Mr. Parrish ?</i>

316
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:12,646
- Yes ?
- Dinner's served.

317
00:23:14,359 --> 00:23:18,261
Yeah.
Never mind.

318
00:23:18,363 --> 00:23:20,263
Leave it to me.

319
00:23:26,138 --> 00:23:29,039
[ Bill's Voice ]
Did you miss me, Bill ?

320
00:23:31,042 --> 00:23:33,010
Chow time, you guys.

321
00:23:35,046 --> 00:23:37,514
What are you looking
so provoked about ?

322
00:23:38,617 --> 00:23:40,881
Did you miss me ?

323
00:23:40,986 --> 00:23:43,284
It's a normal question.

324
00:23:43,388 --> 00:23:47,017
I missed you.
But what do I get back ?

325
00:23:47,125 --> 00:23:49,252
''Not an ounce of excitement.

326
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:51,261
''Not a whisper of a thrill.

327
00:23:52,831 --> 00:23:56,426
This relationship
has all the passion
of a pair of titmice.''

328
00:23:59,504 --> 00:24:01,802
I'm waiting outside
the front door.

329
00:24:01,907 --> 00:24:03,807
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Did you speak</i>
<i>to the governor?</i>

330
00:24:03,909 --> 00:24:06,605
He's coming.
And his wife ?

331
00:24:06,711 --> 00:24:09,043
Yeah, unfortunately.

332
00:24:09,147 --> 00:24:12,241
I sat between them
at the Bronx Zoo benefit.
It was better than Seconal.

333
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:16,047
[ Bill's Voice ]
I'm waiting outside
the front door, Bill.

334
00:24:17,722 --> 00:24:20,156
Won't someone let me in ?

335
00:24:21,693 --> 00:24:23,593
Lillian ?

336
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,891
Is there somebody
at the front door ?
I didn't hear a ring, sir.

337
00:24:31,002 --> 00:24:32,902
Have a look,
would you, please ?

338
00:24:34,005 --> 00:24:35,905
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>What about the mayor?</i>

339
00:24:36,007 --> 00:24:38,601
<i>[ Quince ] He said he's going</i>
<i>to be there with bells on.</i>
<i>[ Drew ] Good.</i>

340
00:24:38,710 --> 00:24:41,144
<i>-Maybe they'll drown him out.</i>
-Please don't be negative, Drew.

341
00:24:41,246 --> 00:24:45,512
<i>[ Drew ] I'm sorry.</i>
We have an acceptance list that
would do the White House proud:

342
00:24:45,617 --> 00:24:49,018
the chairman of the F.C.C.,
the Secretary General
of the U.N.,

343
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:51,213
<i>[ Quince ] Wow.</i>
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>nine senators,</i>

344
00:24:51,323 --> 00:24:56,420
<i>I don't know how many</i>
<i>congressmen and at least</i>
<i>1 2 of the Fortune 500.</i>

345
00:24:56,528 --> 00:24:59,895
Any jocks ?
Hmm ?
No.

346
00:24:59,998 --> 00:25:03,434
No 20-game-winner,
Masters champion,
someone I can talk to ?

347
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:09,330
You were right, Mr. Parrish.
There was a gentleman
at the door.

348
00:25:09,441 --> 00:25:11,909
<i>He's waiting for you</i>
<i>in the foyer.</i>

349
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:18,782
Show him into the library.
Tell him I'll be right there.
<i>[ Lillian ] Yes, sir.</i>

350
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:22,342
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>I've arranged favors, silver</i>
<i>charm bracelets for the women,</i>

351
00:25:22,454 --> 00:25:24,615
<i>[ Drew ] Mmm.</i>
<i>and platinum key chains</i>
<i>for the men,</i>

352
00:25:24,723 --> 00:25:27,283
all engraved ''W.P.''

353
00:25:27,392 --> 00:25:31,226
But now I'm thinking
of scrubbing them.
They seem so ordinary.

354
00:25:31,329 --> 00:25:33,695
<i>Are they ordinary ?</i>

355
00:25:33,798 --> 00:25:35,698
<i>Do they seem that way</i>
<i>to you, Daddy ?</i>

356
00:25:36,801 --> 00:25:38,701
I don't know.

357
00:25:38,803 --> 00:25:41,533
I don't know.
I, uh--

358
00:25:49,047 --> 00:25:51,140
Let me see.

359
00:25:51,249 --> 00:25:53,149
I don't think
they're ordinary.

360
00:25:53,251 --> 00:25:55,344
I think they're great.

361
00:25:55,453 --> 00:25:57,353
I love key chains.

362
00:26:14,205 --> 00:26:16,105
Hello ?

363
00:26:20,211 --> 00:26:22,111
Anyone here ?

364
00:26:25,684 --> 00:26:28,881
I said, is anyone here ?
[ Bill's Voice ]
Quiet down.

365
00:26:35,894 --> 00:26:38,727
Where are you ?
I'm here.

366
00:26:43,335 --> 00:26:45,769
What is this,
a joke, right ?

367
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:48,668
Some kind of elaborate
practical joke ?

368
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:55,806
[ Chuckles ]
At my 40th reunion,
we delivered a casket...

369
00:26:55,914 --> 00:26:59,111
to the class president's
hotel room and, uh--

370
00:26:59,217 --> 00:27:01,117
Quiet.

371
00:27:07,859 --> 00:27:11,056
Where are you going,
Bill ?

372
00:27:11,162 --> 00:27:13,392
I, uh--

373
00:27:13,498 --> 00:27:16,331
The great Bill Parrish
at a loss for words ?

374
00:27:16,434 --> 00:27:21,303
The man from whose lips fall
''rapture'' and ''passion''
and ''obsession'' ?

375
00:27:21,406 --> 00:27:25,308
All those admonitions about
being ''deliriously happy,

376
00:27:25,410 --> 00:27:28,072
that there is no sense
living your life without.''

377
00:27:28,179 --> 00:27:30,079
All the sparks and energy
you give off,

378
00:27:30,181 --> 00:27:34,345
the rosy advice you dispense
in round, pear-shaped tones.

379
00:27:40,091 --> 00:27:42,184
What the hell is this ?

380
00:27:42,293 --> 00:27:44,193
<i>[ Creaking ]</i>

381
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:53,369
Who are you ?

382
00:27:55,340 --> 00:27:58,104
Just think of millenniums
multiplied by eons...

383
00:27:58,209 --> 00:28:00,769
compounded by time without end.

384
00:28:00,879 --> 00:28:02,972
I've been around that long.

385
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:07,848
But it's only recently
that your affairs here
have piqued my interest.

386
00:28:07,952 --> 00:28:10,250
<i>Call it boredom.</i>

387
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:13,017
<i>The natural curiosity of me,</i>
<i>the most lasting...</i>

388
00:28:13,124 --> 00:28:17,618
<i>and significant</i>
<i>element in existence,</i>
<i>has come to see you.</i>

389
00:28:19,431 --> 00:28:21,331
About what ?

390
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:26,161
I want to have a look around
before I take you.

391
00:28:28,139 --> 00:28:30,039
Take me where ?

392
00:28:31,342 --> 00:28:35,244
It requires competence,
wisdom and experience.

393
00:28:35,346 --> 00:28:38,975
All those things they say
about you in testimonials.

394
00:28:39,084 --> 00:28:41,018
And you're the one.

395
00:28:42,420 --> 00:28:44,888
The one to do what ?
<i>Show me around,</i>

396
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:48,618
be my guide.

397
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:51,890
And in return, you get--

398
00:28:54,332 --> 00:28:56,232
I get what ?

399
00:28:58,002 --> 00:29:00,095
Time:

400
00:29:00,205 --> 00:29:03,333
minutes, days, weeks.

401
00:29:03,441 --> 00:29:05,341
Let's not get encumbered
by detail.

402
00:29:05,443 --> 00:29:08,378
<i>What matters is</i>
<i>that I stay interested.</i>

403
00:29:14,686 --> 00:29:16,620
Yes.

404
00:29:19,023 --> 00:29:20,923
''Yes'' what ?

405
00:29:21,025 --> 00:29:24,119
<i>Yes is the answer</i>
<i>to your question.</i>

406
00:29:27,465 --> 00:29:29,365
What question ?
<i>Oh, Bill.</i>

407
00:29:29,467 --> 00:29:32,197
Come on.
The question.

408
00:29:32,303 --> 00:29:36,171
The question you've been
asking yourself with
increased regularity,

409
00:29:36,274 --> 00:29:39,368
at odd moments, panting through
the extra game of handball,

410
00:29:39,477 --> 00:29:41,570
<i>when you ran for the plane</i>
<i>in Delhi,</i>

411
00:29:41,679 --> 00:29:45,206
<i>when you sat up in bed</i>
<i>last night and hit the floor</i>
<i>in the office this morning.</i>

412
00:29:45,316 --> 00:29:48,877
The question that is in
the back of your throat,

413
00:29:48,987 --> 00:29:51,387
choking the blood
to your brain,

414
00:29:51,489 --> 00:29:57,257
ringing in your ears
over and over as you
put it to yourself.

415
00:29:59,531 --> 00:30:01,590
''The question.''
<i>Yes, Bill.</i>

416
00:30:01,699 --> 00:30:03,599
''The question.''

417
00:30:09,107 --> 00:30:11,007
The question.

418
00:30:16,481 --> 00:30:18,381
Am I going to die ?

419
00:30:28,459 --> 00:30:30,359
[ Regular Voice ]
Yes.

420
00:30:36,801 --> 00:30:38,826
Am I dreaming this ?

421
00:30:38,937 --> 00:30:40,837
Are you a dream ?

422
00:30:42,106 --> 00:30:44,006
I'm not a dream.

423
00:30:45,210 --> 00:30:47,110
<i>You're coming to take me ?</i>

424
00:30:48,613 --> 00:30:50,513
What is that ?

425
00:30:50,615 --> 00:30:52,515
And who the hell are you ?

426
00:31:23,948 --> 00:31:25,848
You are--

427
00:31:27,085 --> 00:31:29,212
Yes ?

428
00:31:33,691 --> 00:31:35,818
Who am I ?

429
00:31:45,503 --> 00:31:47,403
Death.

430
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:54,210
You're Death ?

431
00:31:55,847 --> 00:31:58,441
Yes.

432
00:32:04,122 --> 00:32:07,558
Death.
That's me.

433
00:32:09,827 --> 00:32:11,727
You're not Death.
You're just a kid
in a suit.

434
00:32:11,829 --> 00:32:14,730
The suit came with
the body I took.

435
00:32:14,832 --> 00:32:17,596
Let me ask your opinion.

436
00:32:17,702 --> 00:32:19,602
Do I blend in ?

437
00:32:24,542 --> 00:32:26,908
You want me
to be your guide ?

438
00:32:27,011 --> 00:32:29,036
You fill the bill,
Bill.

439
00:32:29,147 --> 00:32:31,047
I do ?
Mmm.

440
00:32:32,884 --> 00:32:34,784
Will you
be staying long ?

441
00:32:34,886 --> 00:32:36,877
We should hope
quite a while.

442
00:32:38,756 --> 00:32:40,656
And then ?

443
00:32:47,298 --> 00:32:49,198
It's over.

444
00:32:50,601 --> 00:32:53,126
It's over.

445
00:32:53,237 --> 00:32:55,797
<i>Mr. Parrish ?</i>

446
00:32:55,907 --> 00:32:57,841
Will the gentleman be staying
for dinner, sir ?

447
00:32:59,811 --> 00:33:01,642
Yes.

448
00:33:05,783 --> 00:33:07,683
Thank you.

449
00:33:11,622 --> 00:33:13,522
This is crazy.

450
00:33:15,927 --> 00:33:17,827
You're not gonna
eat dinner with us.

451
00:33:17,929 --> 00:33:21,365
No, I am eating dinner
with you...
and your family.

452
00:33:21,466 --> 00:33:23,366
And that is what
we're doing.

453
00:33:23,468 --> 00:33:27,632
It's not open
for discussion,
nothing is.

454
00:33:27,739 --> 00:33:30,299
Don't you understand ?

455
00:33:33,244 --> 00:33:35,542
Yeah.

456
00:33:35,646 --> 00:33:37,773
Good.

457
00:33:37,882 --> 00:33:39,782
Now lead the way.

458
00:33:41,119 --> 00:33:43,815
Bill,

459
00:33:43,921 --> 00:33:45,821
lead the way.

460
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:58,132
Excuse me,
may I say something ?
Yes, of course.

461
00:33:58,236 --> 00:34:00,431
Well, it just occurred
to me, if, uh--

462
00:34:00,538 --> 00:34:02,369
Speak up, please.

463
00:34:02,473 --> 00:34:07,308
When I introduce you,
if I say who you are,

464
00:34:07,412 --> 00:34:10,313
I don't think anyone
will stay for dinner.

465
00:34:11,416 --> 00:34:13,350
Then don't.

466
00:34:13,451 --> 00:34:15,578
Here's another possibility.

467
00:34:15,686 --> 00:34:19,622
It's a little last minute,
but tell me what you think.

468
00:34:19,724 --> 00:34:21,624
Kaleidoscopes.

469
00:34:22,860 --> 00:34:24,851
Little gold kaleidoscopes.

470
00:34:24,962 --> 00:34:27,760
Some German company
went kerplunk, and Tiffany's
picked all these things up,

471
00:34:27,865 --> 00:34:30,698
and they're perfect
party favors.

472
00:34:30,802 --> 00:34:33,930
Okay, they're not
personalized or anything.
They're just winter scenes--

473
00:34:34,038 --> 00:34:35,938
dachshunds, snowflakes.

474
00:34:39,710 --> 00:34:41,610
Hi there.

475
00:34:43,981 --> 00:34:45,881
Hello.

476
00:34:47,051 --> 00:34:50,282
Sorry to have...
stepped away for so long.

477
00:34:50,388 --> 00:34:53,516
This is a friend of mine
I asked to drop by.

478
00:34:53,624 --> 00:34:57,025
We got to talking
and stuff, and, uh--

479
00:34:58,796 --> 00:35:00,696
He's gonna join us
for dinner.

480
00:35:03,401 --> 00:35:06,165
Great.
How nice to meet you.

481
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:09,364
And wouldn't it be nicer
if my father would
introduce you ?

482
00:35:10,708 --> 00:35:12,608
How nice to meet you.

483
00:35:14,479 --> 00:35:18,142
Yeah, I'm sorry.
This is my daughter, Allison,
and her husband, Quince,

484
00:35:18,249 --> 00:35:21,013
<i>and Drew, my number one,</i>
<i>works with me.</i>

485
00:35:22,653 --> 00:35:24,917
Daddy, does your friend
have a name ?

486
00:35:25,022 --> 00:35:29,618
- A name ?
- Something he goes by ?

487
00:35:31,996 --> 00:35:34,658
Oh, yeah, excuse me.
This is, uh--

488
00:35:34,765 --> 00:35:36,665
This is, um--

489
00:35:36,767 --> 00:35:39,793
Daddy, come on. A name.
Bill, the suspense
is killing me.

490
00:35:39,904 --> 00:35:42,805
I'm sorry. It's, uh--
It's gone right out
of my head. Um--

491
00:35:45,009 --> 00:35:48,410
I'm sorry.
This is...Joe.

492
00:35:48,513 --> 00:35:51,812
- <i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Joe. I love that name.</i>
-Just plain Joe.

493
00:35:51,916 --> 00:35:54,510
Me too.
Hey, buddy.

494
00:35:55,953 --> 00:35:59,753
- Is there any more to it ?
- What do you mean ?

495
00:35:59,857 --> 00:36:02,826
Like ''Smith''
or ''Jones'' or--

496
00:36:07,798 --> 00:36:10,926
Black.
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Oh, at last.</i>

497
00:36:11,035 --> 00:36:14,232
Nice to meet you,
Mr. Black.
Hey, hey,Joe Black.

498
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:17,273
Won 1 5, lost 2
for the Brooklyn Dodgers, 1 952.

499
00:36:17,375 --> 00:36:19,275
<i>I'm king of</i>
<i>my rotisserie league.</i>

500
00:36:19,377 --> 00:36:22,141
Are you ?
Yeah, he is.

501
00:36:23,748 --> 00:36:26,114
Shall we sit down ?

502
00:36:26,217 --> 00:36:28,117
Right there.

503
00:37:14,599 --> 00:37:17,932
[ Sniffing ]
Have we met ?

504
00:37:19,704 --> 00:37:23,196
- He's from out of town.
- How long you here for,Joe ?

505
00:37:24,342 --> 00:37:27,038
As long as it takes.

506
00:37:29,213 --> 00:37:33,081
You and Bill,
you old friends ?
<i>[ Bill ] No.</i>

507
00:37:36,954 --> 00:37:39,388
No, thank you.

508
00:37:39,523 --> 00:37:41,991
I have one, thank you.

509
00:37:42,126 --> 00:37:45,653
- <i>I get the feeling you've done</i>
<i>some business before.</i>
- I got it.

510
00:37:47,365 --> 00:37:49,333
Have you done
some business before ?

511
00:37:51,035 --> 00:37:53,162
We have an arrangement now.

512
00:37:57,074 --> 00:38:00,009
What side of the industry
did you say you were on ?

513
00:38:00,144 --> 00:38:02,669
I didn't say.

514
00:38:04,215 --> 00:38:06,115
Joe sounds like
a ringer, Bill.

515
00:38:06,217 --> 00:38:09,118
<i>I have a feeling you guys got</i>
<i>the broad strokes already.</i>

516
00:38:09,220 --> 00:38:11,154
You need any help
with the details ?

517
00:38:13,758 --> 00:38:16,056
I'm sorry,
business at dinner.

518
00:38:17,895 --> 00:38:21,888
Forgive me
for being so rude.
Certainly.

519
00:38:22,033 --> 00:38:23,967
<i>Hi, everybody.</i>
<i>I'm sorry I'm late.</i>

520
00:38:24,068 --> 00:38:27,970
- I had to have dinner
with my department chief.
- You ate ?

521
00:38:28,072 --> 00:38:30,097
I'm here, aren't I ?
I wouldn't miss
a loose ends meeting.

522
00:38:30,241 --> 00:38:33,768
What's on the table
for discussion ?
Party favors, flowers--

523
00:38:33,911 --> 00:38:35,811
Hi, Dad.
Hi.

524
00:38:35,913 --> 00:38:37,813
Hello.
Hi, Drew.

525
00:38:42,753 --> 00:38:45,187
What are you doing here ?

526
00:38:45,289 --> 00:38:47,951
You know each other ?

527
00:38:51,529 --> 00:38:53,963
We've met.

528
00:38:55,533 --> 00:38:58,127
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>
<i>This morning,</i>
<i>the Corinth Coffee Shop.</i>

529
00:38:58,269 --> 00:39:00,897
He was, uh--
He was looking for a doctor.

530
00:39:01,038 --> 00:39:04,735
Well, I guess
he's found one.
<i>[ Susan Chuckling ]</i>

531
00:39:04,875 --> 00:39:06,809
Joe,
you do get around.

532
00:39:06,911 --> 00:39:09,607
That's your name ?
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>And isn't it a lovely one ?</i>

533
00:39:09,747 --> 00:39:13,615
So sturdy, so straight.
Stop it.
[ Laughing ]

534
00:39:13,718 --> 00:39:18,052
<i>Incidentally, Joe,</i>
<i>where are you staying ?</i>

535
00:39:19,357 --> 00:39:22,417
- Here.
- You're staying here ?

536
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:28,021
- In this house ?
- Yes, in this house.

537
00:39:28,165 --> 00:39:32,124
<i>[ Quince ]</i>
<i>Great. Great.</i>
<i>Great.</i>

538
00:39:32,269 --> 00:39:34,931
Will that hold you,Joe ?

539
00:39:35,072 --> 00:39:37,165
Incidentally,Joe what ?

540
00:39:37,308 --> 00:39:39,367
Black.

541
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:41,444
This is fun.

542
00:39:41,579 --> 00:39:44,275
Yes.
Yes, Quince, it is.
[ Chuckling ]

543
00:39:44,415 --> 00:39:46,542
So, what are you doing
here,Joe ?

544
00:39:54,658 --> 00:39:57,218
Cat got your tongue ?

545
00:39:57,361 --> 00:40:00,023
[ Chuckling ]
You weren't so silent
this morning.

546
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:04,461
This morning, yes.

547
00:40:06,303 --> 00:40:08,203
I wasn't quite myself.

548
00:40:09,774 --> 00:40:14,177
Well, it's a shame
whoever you were
couldn't be here tonight.

549
00:40:14,311 --> 00:40:16,302
<i>Cut it out, Susan.</i>
<i>We've gotta talk.</i>

550
00:40:16,447 --> 00:40:19,007
<i>Busy day tomorrow,</i>
<i>everybody.</i>

551
00:40:20,684 --> 00:40:23,312
Joe, let's go.

552
00:40:23,454 --> 00:40:25,354
Yes.

553
00:40:34,231 --> 00:40:37,496
That stuff between
you and Susan threw me.

554
00:40:37,635 --> 00:40:39,535
Threw you ?
Where ?

555
00:40:39,637 --> 00:40:41,537
Shook me up.

556
00:40:43,007 --> 00:40:45,601
I mean, how is it
that you happened
to meet my daughter ?

557
00:40:45,743 --> 00:40:47,836
I didn't meet her.

558
00:40:47,978 --> 00:40:49,878
The young man I took
met her.

559
00:40:49,980 --> 00:40:53,381
That is, the fellow
she encountered in
the coffee shop this morning.

560
00:40:54,852 --> 00:40:56,717
What happened to him ?

561
00:40:56,854 --> 00:40:59,789
I needed a body, Bill.

562
00:41:03,694 --> 00:41:05,559
So,

563
00:41:08,933 --> 00:41:10,833
come in.

564
00:41:13,370 --> 00:41:19,036
Uh, bathroom,
tub, towels, sauna,

565
00:41:19,176 --> 00:41:22,168
chairs, lamps, bed.

566
00:41:38,195 --> 00:41:40,789
Well, if there
is anything else,

567
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:45,300
don't hesitate.
I won't.

568
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:51,140
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

569
00:42:48,232 --> 00:42:51,895
<i>[ Water Running ]</i>
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

570
00:42:52,002 --> 00:42:54,903
<i>[ Dishes Clattering ]</i>

571
00:43:00,244 --> 00:43:02,678
I can try.
Will she be available
next week ?

572
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:04,680
I don't know.

573
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:08,351
Yes, sir ?

574
00:43:08,452 --> 00:43:11,250
Hello.
I'm Joe Black.

575
00:43:11,355 --> 00:43:13,255
It's nice meeting you.

576
00:43:13,357 --> 00:43:15,587
Yes, of course,
Mr. Black, sir.

577
00:43:15,693 --> 00:43:18,093
A pleasure.

578
00:43:18,195 --> 00:43:20,095
Eh--

579
00:43:21,198 --> 00:43:23,462
What is that ?

580
00:43:23,567 --> 00:43:25,831
You mean this, sir ?
Yes.

581
00:43:25,936 --> 00:43:29,394
It's, uh, Laura Scudder's
peanut butter, sir.

582
00:43:31,475 --> 00:43:33,375
You like it ?

583
00:43:33,477 --> 00:43:36,071
Well, I would say,
in my opinion,

584
00:43:36,180 --> 00:43:40,173
it's right up there
with Jif and Skippy.

585
00:43:40,284 --> 00:43:42,184
Could I offer you
a taste, sir ?

586
00:43:43,954 --> 00:43:45,854
Yes.
All right.

587
00:44:01,038 --> 00:44:02,903
[ Sniffing ]

588
00:44:12,383 --> 00:44:14,283
[ Coughs ]

589
00:44:20,090 --> 00:44:21,990
Do you fancy it, sir ?

590
00:44:24,395 --> 00:44:27,057
[ Chuckles ]
More ?

591
00:44:27,164 --> 00:44:29,064
Right.

592
00:44:37,808 --> 00:44:39,708
Mmm.

593
00:44:42,413 --> 00:44:45,177
Mmm.
[ Chuckling ]

594
00:44:45,282 --> 00:44:48,080
You're a peanut butter man
now, eh, sir ?

595
00:44:50,220 --> 00:44:52,814
Yes,
I believe I am.

596
00:44:54,124 --> 00:44:56,592
I thoroughly enjoy
this peanut butter.

597
00:44:58,028 --> 00:45:00,189
And I thoroughly enjoyed
meeting you all.

598
00:45:01,598 --> 00:45:04,499
I'll be moseying on.
Right, sir.

599
00:45:12,109 --> 00:45:15,010
<i>[ Water Splashing ]</i>

600
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:38,300
What are you doing here ?

601
00:45:40,771 --> 00:45:43,171
I'm lost.

602
00:45:45,542 --> 00:45:47,635
I can't seem
to escape you today.

603
00:45:47,745 --> 00:45:51,408
I'm sorry.
<i>[ Susan ]</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

604
00:46:11,201 --> 00:46:13,101
Would you hand me
one of those ?

605
00:46:29,219 --> 00:46:33,781
You must have something
very... big going on
with my father.

606
00:46:33,891 --> 00:46:35,791
Big ?
Yeah.

607
00:46:36,994 --> 00:46:39,360
You appear at his side
out of the blue,

608
00:46:39,463 --> 00:46:41,431
stay at his house,
have dinner with his family.

609
00:46:41,532 --> 00:46:45,525
That's, uh,
practically a first.

610
00:46:45,636 --> 00:46:48,969
You're in the red-hot center
of big business,

611
00:46:49,072 --> 00:46:50,972
and I thought you were
just a regular Joe.

612
00:46:52,543 --> 00:46:56,536
I am Joe.
[ Chuckles ]
Not the one that I met
this morning.

613
00:46:56,647 --> 00:47:00,913
Hitting on me in as nice
a way as I've been hit on
in a long time.

614
00:47:01,018 --> 00:47:04,954
The second that you found out
I was my father's daughter,
you, uh--

615
00:47:05,055 --> 00:47:09,788
[ Sniffing ]
Well, you acted
like a stranger.

616
00:47:09,893 --> 00:47:12,293
That is not my intention.

617
00:47:14,064 --> 00:47:16,464
What are your intentions ?

618
00:47:16,567 --> 00:47:20,264
Huh ?
I mean, just to, uh,

619
00:47:20,370 --> 00:47:23,703
make little dramas
in coffee shops,
turn a woman's head ?

620
00:47:23,807 --> 00:47:26,605
I don't mind admitting
that my-my head was turned.

621
00:47:26,710 --> 00:47:29,076
I-I liked it.

622
00:47:29,179 --> 00:47:34,082
But, well, ten hours later,
I feel like a fool.

623
00:47:35,185 --> 00:47:37,585
I just don't get it.
I don't.

624
00:47:37,688 --> 00:47:39,952
You, my father,
here in this house.
It's, uh--

625
00:47:40,057 --> 00:47:43,993
It's upsetting me,
and I--

626
00:47:44,094 --> 00:47:48,030
What happened
to that sweet guy
from the coffee shop ?

627
00:47:49,333 --> 00:47:51,233
Who are you, anyway ?

628
00:47:52,703 --> 00:47:56,662
And...
what are you eating ?

629
00:47:58,141 --> 00:48:00,041
Peanut butter.

630
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:04,780
Hmm.

631
00:48:04,882 --> 00:48:06,782
But it's gone now.

632
00:48:12,589 --> 00:48:14,489
Wh-- No. Please.

633
00:48:16,627 --> 00:48:19,790
You act like you've never had
peanut butter before.
I haven't.

634
00:48:21,265 --> 00:48:23,995
What kind of childhood
did you have ?
Do you love Drew ?

635
00:48:24,101 --> 00:48:26,194
Excuse me ?

636
00:48:26,303 --> 00:48:29,238
When you put your mouth
to his, it seemed
a frequent thing.

637
00:48:32,009 --> 00:48:34,068
Drew is
none of your business,

638
00:48:34,177 --> 00:48:36,839
and neither is where
I put my mouth.

639
00:48:36,947 --> 00:48:39,211
I'm sorry.
Do you live here ?

640
00:48:39,316 --> 00:48:42,308
No,Joe, I'm swimming here
and now I'm going home.

641
00:48:42,419 --> 00:48:45,582
Yes, I think what
I'm trying to say is,

642
00:48:45,689 --> 00:48:48,317
I would like it
if we were friends.

643
00:48:48,425 --> 00:48:51,019
I've got
plenty of friends.

644
00:48:51,128 --> 00:48:53,756
I don't have any.

645
00:48:55,999 --> 00:48:58,365
Well, I can see why.

646
00:49:05,375 --> 00:49:07,741
I didn't mean
to offend you at dinner.

647
00:49:07,844 --> 00:49:10,142
I'm sometimes...

648
00:49:10,247 --> 00:49:14,013
not quite at home
around people.

649
00:49:15,986 --> 00:49:19,422
I get busy doing, uh,
what it is I do.

650
00:49:19,523 --> 00:49:23,516
And I don't seem
to have developed--

651
00:49:26,596 --> 00:49:28,723
Yes ?

652
00:49:32,836 --> 00:49:38,604
I have a certain function
to perform, and it seems
to take up most of my time.

653
00:49:39,977 --> 00:49:43,879
But sometimes I...
speculate...

654
00:49:46,416 --> 00:49:48,748
that I haven't
left room for...

655
00:49:51,722 --> 00:49:54,088
anything else.

656
00:49:57,594 --> 00:49:59,494
Hmm.

657
00:50:01,031 --> 00:50:03,329
I'm sorry to say
I know what you mean.

658
00:50:16,380 --> 00:50:18,280
Well, um--

659
00:50:21,284 --> 00:50:23,184
Good night,Joe.

660
00:50:23,286 --> 00:50:25,686
Yes.

661
00:50:25,789 --> 00:50:28,553
Good night to you,
Susan.

662
00:50:30,961 --> 00:50:33,486
Morning, Madeline.
Oh, good morning,
Mr. Parrish.

663
00:50:33,597 --> 00:50:36,122
Everything okay ?
Yes, sir.

664
00:50:36,233 --> 00:50:38,133
Good.

665
00:50:55,552 --> 00:50:57,816
Morning.

666
00:50:57,921 --> 00:51:00,219
Good morning, Bill.

667
00:51:05,829 --> 00:51:08,491
What's on the docket
for today ?

668
00:51:08,598 --> 00:51:13,194
Docket ?
Hmm, yes.
What shall we do ?

669
00:51:13,303 --> 00:51:17,137
Well, I have to
go to work, and--
Splendid. I'll join you.

670
00:51:17,240 --> 00:51:19,174
Oh.

671
00:51:19,276 --> 00:51:21,801
[ Chuckles ]
Would you like
to ride or walk ?

672
00:51:21,912 --> 00:51:25,439
Walk. I wish
to see the world.

673
00:51:25,549 --> 00:51:30,145
This is crazy.
This is the left field
thing of all time.

674
00:51:30,253 --> 00:51:33,745
I, uh--
I don't know if
I can get through this.

675
00:51:33,857 --> 00:51:37,054
- What do I do ?
What do I tell my family ?
- You'll get through this, Bill.

676
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:40,652
As far as
your family's concerned, uh,
I wouldn't say anything.

677
00:51:40,764 --> 00:51:43,699
You'll ruin the great start
we had last night.

678
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:48,328
Hmm. It felt as if
I was being treated
like a person.

679
00:51:48,438 --> 00:51:50,372
Yes,Joe this,Joe that.

680
00:51:50,474 --> 00:51:54,604
A nice smile.
Quince passed me the rolls.

681
00:51:54,711 --> 00:51:59,705
No passion or rapture
or any of these mighty things
you're so intent on imparting.

682
00:51:59,816 --> 00:52:01,875
But I am certain,

683
00:52:01,985 --> 00:52:05,079
should you say who I am,
our adventure would
end abruptly.

684
00:52:05,188 --> 00:52:07,588
Mm-hmm.

685
00:52:11,027 --> 00:52:14,019
And I did so enjoy
your family.

686
00:52:16,533 --> 00:52:20,299
What about my family ?
This adventure involves
only me, right ?

687
00:52:20,403 --> 00:52:23,270
What do you mean ?

688
00:52:26,643 --> 00:52:29,840
I'll tell you what.
You promise this undertaking
of yours...

689
00:52:29,946 --> 00:52:31,880
involves only me
and, uh--

690
00:52:31,982 --> 00:52:34,382
And what ?

691
00:52:34,484 --> 00:52:37,146
I won't tell anyone
who you are.
Sounds fair enough.

692
00:52:37,254 --> 00:52:40,485
Good.
Is it a deal ?

693
00:52:40,590 --> 00:52:43,218
A deal ?
Yeah.

694
00:52:43,326 --> 00:52:46,295
You give your word;
I give mine that we'll
do what we say.

695
00:52:46,396 --> 00:52:50,162
Mm-hmm.
It is a truth exchanged
between two people.

696
00:52:50,267 --> 00:52:52,326
Bill ?
What ?

697
00:52:52,435 --> 00:52:55,529
You have a deal.
Ow !

698
00:53:02,145 --> 00:53:04,705
That's great.

699
00:53:07,517 --> 00:53:09,644
Great.

700
00:53:09,753 --> 00:53:13,416
You know,
I got to thinking.

701
00:53:13,523 --> 00:53:17,653
With you here
and seemingly occupied,

702
00:53:17,761 --> 00:53:20,753
how's your work going,
I mean, elsewhere ?

703
00:53:20,864 --> 00:53:24,698
While you were shaving
this morning, you weren't
just shaving.

704
00:53:24,801 --> 00:53:28,100
What do you mean ?
You were hatching ideas,

705
00:53:28,205 --> 00:53:31,140
making plans,
arriving at decisions,
right ?

706
00:53:31,241 --> 00:53:33,175
Yeah, I guess so.

707
00:53:33,276 --> 00:53:36,973
So you understand the concept.
While part of you is busy
doing one thing,

708
00:53:37,080 --> 00:53:41,676
another part of you is doing
another, perhaps even attending
to the problems of your work.

709
00:53:41,785 --> 00:53:44,618
Correct ?
Of course.

710
00:53:44,721 --> 00:53:48,384
So you understand the idea.
Congratulations, Bill.

711
00:53:48,491 --> 00:53:51,654
Now multiply that
by infinity, take that
to the depths of forever,

712
00:53:51,761 --> 00:53:54,423
and you still will barely
have a glimpse of what
I'm talking about.

713
00:53:54,531 --> 00:53:57,056
<i>[ Horn Honking ]</i>

714
00:54:01,371 --> 00:54:03,862
Joe ?
Yes, Bill ?

715
00:54:06,610 --> 00:54:09,010
How about giving
a guy a break ?

716
00:54:09,112 --> 00:54:11,080
Make an exception ?

717
00:54:11,181 --> 00:54:14,548
Well, there's one
to every rule.
Not this.

718
00:54:14,651 --> 00:54:17,620
And call my family.
I'd like them to have
dinner with me tonight.

719
00:54:17,721 --> 00:54:20,952
Didn't the family
get together last night ?

720
00:54:21,057 --> 00:54:25,391
Jennifer.
Of course, Mr. Parrish,
right away.

721
00:54:25,495 --> 00:54:28,362
Uh, perhaps you'd like
to wait in my office.
No.

722
00:54:28,465 --> 00:54:32,333
What I'm trying to say
is this is a board meeting
and you're not a member.

723
00:54:32,435 --> 00:54:36,098
I'm sure you'll find a way
to make it all right.
[ Sighs ]

724
00:54:36,206 --> 00:54:39,266
Nice to meet you.

725
00:54:39,376 --> 00:54:41,310
Morning.

726
00:54:41,411 --> 00:54:43,345
[ All ]
Good morning.

727
00:54:45,815 --> 00:54:47,806
Thank you.
Eddie.

728
00:54:47,917 --> 00:54:50,215
Uh, this is Joe Black.

729
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:55,314
He's a personal associate
of mine, and, uh--
Hello, Quince.

730
00:54:55,425 --> 00:54:57,859
Hey.
<i>[ Bill ] He'll be</i>
<i>joining us this morning.</i>

731
00:54:57,961 --> 00:55:02,193
<i>I know this is unusual,</i>
<i>and my apologies, and, uh--</i>

732
00:55:02,299 --> 00:55:05,166
Drew, carry on.
<i>[ Drew ]</i>
<i>It's nice to see you.</i>

733
00:55:05,268 --> 00:55:08,396
Didn't expect you,
but, uh--

734
00:55:08,505 --> 00:55:10,530
certainly you can't get
enough of a good thing.

735
00:55:10,640 --> 00:55:14,167
Thank you.
Joe, would you like
to sit there ?

736
00:55:14,277 --> 00:55:16,973
[ Chewing ]

737
00:55:25,855 --> 00:55:27,789
Okay.

738
00:55:27,891 --> 00:55:32,351
<i>Uh, the Board</i>
<i>of Parrish Communications</i>
<i>is hereby called to order.</i>

739
00:55:32,462 --> 00:55:34,396
Our sole order of--

740
00:55:40,170 --> 00:55:42,900
Our s--

741
00:55:50,146 --> 00:55:52,774
Our sole order
of business today is a, uh--

742
00:55:52,882 --> 00:55:56,045
is an acceptance of
John Bontecou's generous offer.

743
00:55:56,152 --> 00:55:59,019
<i>And I think Bill--</i>
Do you have any more
of these delicious cookies ?

744
00:55:59,122 --> 00:56:01,352
<i>Thejelly ones ?</i>

745
00:56:01,458 --> 00:56:03,653
<i>Mmm, and a cup of tea.</i>

746
00:56:03,760 --> 00:56:08,663
With milk, I think.
I'd like to try it
English style. Yes.

747
00:56:08,765 --> 00:56:10,699
<i>[Joe ]</i>
<i>A cup of tea</i>
<i>with milk, please.</i>

748
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:12,927
Is there anything else,
Mr. Black ?

749
00:56:13,036 --> 00:56:15,368
- How about some water ?
- Why, yes, thank you.

750
00:56:15,472 --> 00:56:17,372
<i>Hot or cold?</i>
Cold.

751
00:56:17,474 --> 00:56:21,376
- And a glass ?
- Mmm.

752
00:56:25,448 --> 00:56:30,078
Uh, to review.
We're really crossing the T's
and dotting the I's here.

753
00:56:30,186 --> 00:56:34,020
Uh, Bill had a great
and conclusive meeting
yesterday with John Bontecou,

754
00:56:34,124 --> 00:56:37,093
and all that remains for us
is to put it to a vote.

755
00:56:39,796 --> 00:56:44,358
Um, thank you.
Drew, um--

756
00:56:45,702 --> 00:56:47,966
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

757
00:56:48,071 --> 00:56:50,938
I did enjoy, or rather
I was interested...

758
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:55,409
in meeting
John Bontecou yesterday,

759
00:56:55,512 --> 00:56:57,605
and, um--

760
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:04,050
Impressive, I suppose.

761
00:57:04,154 --> 00:57:06,054
But, uh--

762
00:57:09,993 --> 00:57:12,427
But--

763
00:57:12,562 --> 00:57:15,963
It did get me to thinking.

764
00:57:17,700 --> 00:57:21,898
<i>See, I started</i>
<i>in this business because</i>
<i>this is what I wanted to do.</i>

765
00:57:22,005 --> 00:57:26,499
I knew I wasn't gonna write
the great American novel.

766
00:57:26,643 --> 00:57:29,908
But I also knew there was
more to life than buying
something for a dollar...

767
00:57:30,013 --> 00:57:32,880
and selling it for two.

768
00:57:32,982 --> 00:57:36,418
<i>I'd hoped</i>
<i>to create something,</i>
<i>something which could be...</i>

769
00:57:36,553 --> 00:57:39,488
held to
the highest standards.

770
00:57:39,589 --> 00:57:43,457
And what I realized
was I--

771
00:57:43,560 --> 00:57:46,859
I wanted to give
the news to the world.

772
00:57:46,963 --> 00:57:51,263
And I wanted
to give it unvarnished.

773
00:57:51,367 --> 00:57:55,770
Uh, the more we all know
about each other, the greater
the chance we will survive.

774
00:57:55,905 --> 00:57:59,568
Sure, I want to make a profit.
You can't exist without one,
but, uh--

775
00:57:59,676 --> 00:58:03,942
[ Chuckles ]
John Bontecou is all profit.

776
00:58:04,047 --> 00:58:08,916
<i>If we give him</i>
<i>license to absorb</i>
<i>Parrish Communications--</i>

777
00:58:09,018 --> 00:58:11,009
<i>and he has his eye</i>
<i>on a few others after us--</i>

778
00:58:11,154 --> 00:58:13,418
in order to reach the world,

779
00:58:13,523 --> 00:58:17,425
you will have to go
through John Bontecou.

780
00:58:17,527 --> 00:58:19,552
And not only will you
have to pay him
to do this,

781
00:58:19,696 --> 00:58:22,961
far more important,
you'll have to
agree with him.

782
00:58:24,734 --> 00:58:28,534
<i>Reporting the news</i>
<i>is a privilege</i>
<i>and a responsibility.</i>

783
00:58:28,638 --> 00:58:32,130
And it is not exploitable.

784
00:58:32,275 --> 00:58:35,472
Parrish Communications
has earned this privilege.

785
00:58:35,578 --> 00:58:38,979
John Bontecou
wants to buy it.

786
00:58:40,517 --> 00:58:43,213
<i>As your chairman,</i>

787
00:58:43,319 --> 00:58:45,787
I urge you to agree.

788
00:58:45,922 --> 00:58:48,982
This company
is not for sale.

789
00:58:54,998 --> 00:58:57,466
It sounds like
you're not leaving
much room for discussion.

790
00:58:57,600 --> 00:58:59,500
Thank you.
You're welcome.

791
00:58:59,602 --> 00:59:02,002
I know. I'm sorry, I--
Looks like I'm
reversing my field.

792
00:59:02,105 --> 00:59:04,665
That's your privilege, Bill.
But given our needs,

793
00:59:04,807 --> 00:59:07,537
given the absolute necessity
for growth, given the future,

794
00:59:07,644 --> 00:59:11,341
the truth is, joining
John Bontecou is every bit
as certain as death and taxes.

795
00:59:11,447 --> 00:59:14,883
Death and taxes ?
<i>Yes.</i>

796
00:59:15,018 --> 00:59:17,714
- <i>Death</i> and taxes ?
- Yes.

797
00:59:17,820 --> 00:59:20,983
What an odd pairing.
<i>It's just a saying,</i>
<i>Mr. Black.</i>

798
00:59:21,090 --> 00:59:23,615
Mmm. By whom ?
<i>Doesn't matter.</i>

799
00:59:23,760 --> 00:59:27,093
- Then why'd
you bring it up ?
- [ Sighs ]

800
00:59:27,196 --> 00:59:29,164
You're not familiar
with the phrase,
''In this world,

801
00:59:29,299 --> 00:59:31,358
nothing is certain
but death and taxes ?''

802
00:59:31,501 --> 00:59:33,992
Well, I am now.
<i>Glad I could be</i>
<i>of some help.</i>

803
00:59:34,137 --> 00:59:37,300
<i>I keep regular office hours</i>
<i>if there's any further</i>
<i>information you might need...</i>

804
00:59:37,407 --> 00:59:40,342
on sayings, common phrases,
manners of speaking.

805
00:59:40,476 --> 00:59:44,742
My door's wide open.
The tea I can provide,
perhaps even the milk.

806
00:59:44,847 --> 00:59:46,872
Low fat.

807
00:59:47,016 --> 00:59:49,007
<i>Yeah, okay, well, uh--</i>

808
00:59:49,152 --> 00:59:52,849
I think we've accomplished
everything we're going to this
morning. Shall we adjourn ?

809
00:59:52,956 --> 00:59:56,858
- But the matter is still
on the table, Bill.
-Joe ?

810
00:59:56,993 --> 00:59:59,518
Yes.

811
01:00:06,336 --> 01:00:08,930
Thank you for
the delicious cookies.

812
01:00:11,374 --> 01:00:14,104
[ Chewing ]
Mmm.

813
01:00:16,546 --> 01:00:19,037
Who is that guy ?

814
01:00:21,050 --> 01:00:22,950
So...

815
01:00:24,354 --> 01:00:26,686
what's the deal here ?

816
01:00:26,789 --> 01:00:29,815
You gonna be
breathing down my neck
right till the very end ?

817
01:00:29,959 --> 01:00:33,360
I don't understand.
I'd like to be alone
for a while.

818
01:00:36,232 --> 01:00:40,669
Are you sad, Bill ?
Yes, I am.

819
01:00:40,803 --> 01:00:42,737
Why don't you take
a walk or something,
get some air ?

820
01:00:42,872 --> 01:00:45,397
I know
I'll be seeing you.

821
01:00:45,541 --> 01:00:49,068
[ Chewing ]
Of course.

822
01:00:49,212 --> 01:00:52,409
Good. Now I'd like
to be alone.

823
01:00:52,548 --> 01:00:54,482
This will hold you
for a while.

824
01:00:54,617 --> 01:00:57,245
You know about money,
don't you ?
It can't buy happiness ?

825
01:00:57,387 --> 01:01:00,185
Yeah.
Uh,Jennifer ?

826
01:01:00,289 --> 01:01:03,486
Give Mr. Black a map
of the city, would you ?
It's okay, Bill.

827
01:01:03,626 --> 01:01:06,789
I can manage.

828
01:01:11,934 --> 01:01:13,834
Hi.
Hi.

829
01:01:13,936 --> 01:01:16,871
I need a medical
record number for labs.
Uh-huh.

830
01:01:17,006 --> 01:01:21,500
And, uh, will you try
calling her husband ?
The number's on top.

831
01:01:27,283 --> 01:01:29,751
Also, can you page me
when C.T.'s ready ?

832
01:01:29,886 --> 01:01:32,446
Oh, sure.
Thanks, sweetie.

833
01:01:35,191 --> 01:01:38,217
How nice you look.
Is that your uniform ?

834
01:01:38,361 --> 01:01:40,829
What are you doing here ?

835
01:01:43,533 --> 01:01:46,696
Are you ill ?
Oh, goodness, no.

836
01:01:46,836 --> 01:01:50,465
Then why
are you here,Joe ?
I'm here to see you.

837
01:01:52,942 --> 01:01:56,503
Joe, I don't--
I don't have time
to see you right now.

838
01:01:56,646 --> 01:01:59,080
I'm, um, about to start
making rounds,

839
01:01:59,182 --> 01:02:02,049
and I'm examining
back-to-back patients
until dinner, and, uh--

840
01:02:02,151 --> 01:02:04,381
Very well. I'll watch.

841
01:02:04,520 --> 01:02:07,648
Watch me do what ?
Make rounds and examine
back-to-back patients.

842
01:02:07,790 --> 01:02:10,987
[ Chuckles ]
Joe, that's impossible.

843
01:02:11,127 --> 01:02:14,563
I'm a doctor.
And I'll be
a visitor.

844
01:02:14,697 --> 01:02:18,531
Patients have visitors,
not doctors.
I don't mind.

845
01:02:18,634 --> 01:02:22,229
[ Chuckles ]
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>Miss ? Miss ?</i>

846
01:02:22,371 --> 01:02:26,171
Doctor.
Oh, um, just one second.
I'll be right there.

847
01:02:26,309 --> 01:02:28,504
Please.
My mama is sicker
than him.

848
01:02:30,413 --> 01:02:32,313
Okay.

849
01:02:36,152 --> 01:02:39,713
- [ Jamaican Accent ]
Obeah.
- <i>No, Mama.</i>

850
01:02:39,856 --> 01:02:42,256
<i>Obeah, man.</i>

851
01:02:42,358 --> 01:02:45,293
- I goin' die.
- Mama, stop it.
It's just a man.

852
01:02:45,394 --> 01:02:48,295
<i>[ Susan ] What's Obeah ?</i>
<i>[ Daughter ] Bad spirit.</i>
<i>Shejust all fever.</i>

853
01:02:48,397 --> 01:02:51,298
She don't mean nothing.
Please help us.
Of course.

854
01:02:51,400 --> 01:02:53,595
<i>[Joe With Jamaican Accent ]</i>
<i>No Obeah, sister.</i>

855
01:02:53,736 --> 01:02:56,170
Everything gonna be
all right.

856
01:03:02,211 --> 01:03:04,736
Have you registered ?
No.

857
01:03:04,881 --> 01:03:07,247
Okay.

858
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:18,954
You gonna be all right ?
Go with the doctor lady.
Mama gonna be fine now.

859
01:03:19,095 --> 01:03:21,586
Don't leave.
Don't leave me.

860
01:03:21,731 --> 01:03:25,132
She'll be
right back, okay ?
Mama.

861
01:03:27,170 --> 01:03:30,139
[ Inhales, Groans ]

862
01:03:33,910 --> 01:03:37,505
- Obeah.
- Rahtid.

863
01:03:37,647 --> 01:03:40,138
Obeah evil.
I not evil, woman.

864
01:03:40,283 --> 01:03:42,649
And what you is then ?

865
01:03:45,254 --> 01:03:47,916
I from that next place.

866
01:03:48,057 --> 01:03:51,151
You waitin' here
to take us ?

867
01:03:51,260 --> 01:03:53,694
Like you is
the bus driver to there ?

868
01:03:53,830 --> 01:03:56,663
No, man,
I on 'oliday.

869
01:03:58,634 --> 01:04:01,626
Some spot you pick.

870
01:04:04,640 --> 01:04:07,541
Oh. Mmm.

871
01:04:07,643 --> 01:04:11,101
The pain.
Pain is bad, bad.

872
01:04:11,214 --> 01:04:15,116
I don't have nothin'
to do with these things,
you know.

873
01:04:15,218 --> 01:04:18,813
Make it go away.
Doctor lady
make it all right.

874
01:04:18,955 --> 01:04:22,721
Uh-uh.
Not this pain.

875
01:04:22,825 --> 01:04:26,488
This pain go
through and through me.

876
01:04:26,596 --> 01:04:28,894
Make it go away.
I can't, sister.

877
01:04:28,998 --> 01:04:32,490
You can, mister.

878
01:04:32,602 --> 01:04:34,502
Take me to
that next place.

879
01:04:34,604 --> 01:04:37,732
It's not your time now.
Make it time.

880
01:04:37,840 --> 01:04:40,172
You can't fool with
the way things
got to be.

881
01:04:40,276 --> 01:04:44,007
[ Whimpering ]
Please ?

882
01:04:48,784 --> 01:04:51,480
[ Quietly ]
Where she was born.

883
01:04:54,257 --> 01:04:57,385
Close your eyes.

884
01:04:57,493 --> 01:04:59,393
Go on, sister.

885
01:05:31,727 --> 01:05:33,922
Soon.

886
01:05:37,967 --> 01:05:40,299
You-- You can go with her.
I'll be right there.

887
01:05:40,403 --> 01:05:42,428
Come now, Mama.

888
01:05:48,110 --> 01:05:51,876
She's in a great deal
of pain.
Yes.

889
01:05:54,951 --> 01:05:59,718
Have you spent much time
in the islands ?
Some.

890
01:06:02,792 --> 01:06:06,159
I realize now
my being here,

891
01:06:06,262 --> 01:06:08,662
uh, is not
quite appropriate.

892
01:06:08,764 --> 01:06:12,564
Oh, no, please--
Please don't apologize.

893
01:06:13,703 --> 01:06:16,866
Yes ?
Yeah.

894
01:06:20,743 --> 01:06:23,075
I'm glad that you came.

895
01:06:23,179 --> 01:06:27,741
Thank you, Susan.
I'm very happy
to be here.

896
01:06:30,152 --> 01:06:33,781
Joe, I'm with Drew.

897
01:06:35,124 --> 01:06:37,592
Not now.

898
01:06:41,330 --> 01:06:44,993
[ Chuckles ]
I have to go.

899
01:06:45,101 --> 01:06:49,265
I'm sorry to say.
Be sorry for nothing.

900
01:06:51,440 --> 01:06:54,807
[ Chuckles ]
Right.

901
01:06:54,910 --> 01:06:59,040
Thanks,Joe.
Good-bye, Susan.

902
01:07:10,960 --> 01:07:15,192
- Good ?
- Mmm.

903
01:07:15,297 --> 01:07:20,064
- Yes, what is it ?
- Cold lamb sandwich
with cilantro.

904
01:07:20,169 --> 01:07:22,865
A little Coleman's mustard.

905
01:07:24,507 --> 01:07:27,032
It's, uh, splendid.

906
01:07:27,143 --> 01:07:29,771
Glad you like it.

907
01:07:32,181 --> 01:07:36,709
My wife turned me on
to cold lamb sandwiches.

908
01:07:38,454 --> 01:07:42,982
-Joan... was my wife.
- Mm-hmm.

909
01:07:55,471 --> 01:07:59,407
Yeah.
Cold lamb sandwiches.

910
01:07:59,508 --> 01:08:04,172
Not as chewy as roast beef,
not as boring as chicken.

911
01:08:04,280 --> 01:08:08,444
<i>She knew stuff like that.</i>

912
01:08:11,387 --> 01:08:13,981
Everything reminds me
of her.

913
01:08:14,090 --> 01:08:18,720
There isn't a day goes by
that I don't think about her.

914
01:08:18,828 --> 01:08:23,697
One day she didn't feel well.
The next day she was gone.

915
01:08:28,070 --> 01:08:30,402
So what
are you gonna do ?

916
01:08:30,506 --> 01:08:34,067
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

917
01:08:34,176 --> 01:08:37,703
I guess you've heard all this
a trillion times before, huh ?

918
01:08:38,881 --> 01:08:42,647
- More.
- Why didn't you stop me ?

919
01:08:42,751 --> 01:08:45,219
I don't know.

920
01:08:48,524 --> 01:08:51,322
What was it like
when you first met ?

921
01:08:52,628 --> 01:08:55,222
I thought you'd heard it
a trillion times before.

922
01:08:55,331 --> 01:08:58,528
This part
I'm interested in.

923
01:09:04,807 --> 01:09:08,243
Well, she had on
this little blue suit...

924
01:09:08,344 --> 01:09:12,144
[ Breathes Heavily ]

925
01:09:12,248 --> 01:09:16,651
with a little white collar
that had a little...

926
01:09:16,752 --> 01:09:19,846
red piping on it.

927
01:09:23,292 --> 01:09:25,487
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>
Yeah ?

928
01:09:27,730 --> 01:09:30,096
Hi.

929
01:09:31,267 --> 01:09:34,202
- Am I interrupting ?
- Yes.

930
01:09:35,604 --> 01:09:38,266
- No.
-Just kidding ?

931
01:09:38,374 --> 01:09:41,707
<i>[ Bill ]</i>
<i>Sit down, Drew.</i>

932
01:09:41,810 --> 01:09:46,304
Uh, before I do,
I was hoping we might
be alone, Bill.

933
01:09:46,415 --> 01:09:49,543
Well,Joe and I have
no secrets from each other.

934
01:09:49,652 --> 01:09:51,552
<i>[ Drew ]</i>
<i>How nice for you both.</i>

935
01:09:55,224 --> 01:09:59,718
Pardon my candor, but I was
confounded by your decision
this morning.

936
01:09:59,828 --> 01:10:01,819
Why ?
I was hired.

937
01:10:01,931 --> 01:10:05,833
You told me to help bring
Parrish Communications
into the 2 1 st century.

938
01:10:05,935 --> 01:10:08,665
This merger is the vehicle.
In my estimation--
<i>Perhaps a merger is a way...</i>

939
01:10:08,771 --> 01:10:12,036
to bring Bill's company
into the 2 1 st century,
and perhaps it isn't.

940
01:10:12,141 --> 01:10:15,201
And perhaps cheating
on your French philosophers
exam at the Groton School...

941
01:10:15,311 --> 01:10:18,906
was an expedient way
to get your diploma,
and perhaps it wasn't.

942
01:10:19,014 --> 01:10:24,475
<i>Be that as it may, Drew,</i>
<i>a question can often</i>
<i>be argued both ways.</i>

943
01:10:24,587 --> 01:10:27,147
Joe, cut it out.
You too, Drew.

944
01:10:30,059 --> 01:10:34,120
- I thought this was
practically a done deal.
- Well, now it's undone, okay ?

945
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:37,324
Forget Bontecou.
Scrub him.

946
01:10:37,433 --> 01:10:40,891
I'm tired of his fancy name
and his fancy offer.

947
01:10:41,003 --> 01:10:44,234
I'm not going for it.

948
01:10:44,340 --> 01:10:47,002
Okay.

949
01:10:55,884 --> 01:10:58,876
<i>Bill,</i>
<i>why at this juncture...</i>

950
01:10:58,988 --> 01:11:03,322
are you letting yourself
be so concerned
by business matters ?

951
01:11:03,425 --> 01:11:07,259
'Cause I don't want anybody
buying up my life's work !

952
01:11:07,363 --> 01:11:10,161
Turning it into something
it wasn't meant to be.

953
01:11:10,266 --> 01:11:14,703
A man wants to leave
something behind. He wants it
left behind the way he made it.

954
01:11:14,803 --> 01:11:16,794
He wants it to be run
the way he ran it,

955
01:11:16,905 --> 01:11:19,396
with a sense of honor,
of dedication, of truth.

956
01:11:19,508 --> 01:11:22,102
Easy, Bill.
You'll give yourself
a heart attack...

957
01:11:22,211 --> 01:11:25,271
and ruin my vacation.

958
01:11:42,898 --> 01:11:44,923
Now listen.

959
01:11:45,034 --> 01:11:47,468
I read you all the way
on the Bontecou thing,

960
01:11:47,569 --> 01:11:51,471
and I know where
you're coming from,
and I am with you 1 01 percent.

961
01:11:51,573 --> 01:11:54,406
Well, thank you,
Quince.

962
01:11:56,979 --> 01:11:59,106
But I just gotta
tell you,

963
01:11:59,214 --> 01:12:01,682
if mergers are
in the wind,

964
01:12:01,784 --> 01:12:05,413
I've developed
some great prospects.

965
01:12:05,521 --> 01:12:08,319
And I want to come
and talk to you about--
about 'em next week.

966
01:12:08,424 --> 01:12:10,619
Next week ?
Yeah.

967
01:12:11,860 --> 01:12:14,988
Or the week after.

968
01:12:16,632 --> 01:12:19,829
No good ?
No. Why,
anything's possible.

969
01:12:19,935 --> 01:12:23,336
It's up to Joe.
[ Exhales ]
Joe.

970
01:12:23,439 --> 01:12:26,272
You just don't know
how glad I am
you're aboard,

971
01:12:26,375 --> 01:12:28,935
because anybody who can
take some of the weight
off the old man,

972
01:12:29,044 --> 01:12:32,343
I am--
I'm in his corner.

973
01:12:32,448 --> 01:12:36,782
That's very gracious
of you, Quince.
Ah, it's no problem.

974
01:12:36,885 --> 01:12:40,787
Well, I'll leave
you two alone,
because I can, uh--

975
01:12:40,889 --> 01:12:43,323
I can tell, you know--

976
01:12:43,425 --> 01:12:45,484
you got something
in the fire.

977
01:12:51,166 --> 01:12:53,396
Now, look,
I know you're down.

978
01:12:53,502 --> 01:12:57,871
But you know,
when you're down,
there's no place to go but up.

979
01:12:57,973 --> 01:13:00,237
Up.
Thanks, Quince.

980
01:13:00,342 --> 01:13:02,276
Forget about Bontecou.

981
01:13:02,378 --> 01:13:04,778
I got a couple other
merger possibilities
up my sleeve,

982
01:13:04,880 --> 01:13:07,041
and I'm pitching 'em
to the old man.

983
01:13:07,149 --> 01:13:09,083
Were you ?
Yeah.

984
01:13:09,184 --> 01:13:12,347
Hey, listen.
Mm-hmm.

985
01:13:12,454 --> 01:13:15,821
We're gonna
go in together.
I'll clue you in.

986
01:13:15,924 --> 01:13:19,325
[ Stammering ]
The timing has gotta
be right,

987
01:13:19,428 --> 01:13:22,158
because the old man
says it's up to Joe.

988
01:13:25,701 --> 01:13:27,601
He said
it's up to Joe ?
Mm-hmm.

989
01:13:27,703 --> 01:13:30,433
Those were his words ?
Yeah.

990
01:13:30,539 --> 01:13:32,473
It's up to Joe, huh ?
Yeah.

991
01:13:32,574 --> 01:13:36,169
That's what he said ?
That's what he--
That's what he said.

992
01:13:36,278 --> 01:13:39,213
That's very interesting.

993
01:13:39,314 --> 01:13:42,374
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I thought so too.

994
01:13:42,484 --> 01:13:46,011
[ Glass Ringing ]

995
01:13:46,121 --> 01:13:48,021
[ Chuckles ]

996
01:13:50,159 --> 01:13:53,788
I want to thank you all
for coming.

997
01:13:53,896 --> 01:13:57,024
Uh, my family, um,
Allison and Quince,

998
01:13:57,132 --> 01:13:59,396
Susan and
the other members.

999
01:14:02,704 --> 01:14:04,763
And, uh--

1000
01:14:05,874 --> 01:14:08,399
So glad when we
can get together.

1001
01:14:08,510 --> 01:14:12,139
I mean, I know
you all have busy lives.

1002
01:14:12,247 --> 01:14:14,807
- Look who's talking.
- Yeah. Speak for yourself.

1003
01:14:14,917 --> 01:14:17,351
Yeah.
[ Clicks Tongue ]

1004
01:14:17,453 --> 01:14:22,117
I remember when
you were little girls,
and, uh--

1005
01:14:22,224 --> 01:14:24,920
I love little girls.

1006
01:14:27,062 --> 01:14:31,863
And uh, now you're
all grown up,
and I, um--

1007
01:14:31,967 --> 01:14:35,095
I had some words prepared,
but, uh,

1008
01:14:35,204 --> 01:14:37,104
I've forgotten them.

1009
01:14:37,206 --> 01:14:40,607
Um--
Wait a minute, uh--

1010
01:14:44,413 --> 01:14:46,973
There's so much
I wanted to say, uh--
<i>[ Allison ] Daddy ?</i>

1011
01:14:47,082 --> 01:14:51,610
- You could sit down
if you want to.
- Yeah.

1012
01:14:51,720 --> 01:14:54,587
So many words I wanted to--

1013
01:14:54,690 --> 01:14:57,124
So much I wanted to say,
but, uh--

1014
01:14:59,561 --> 01:15:02,223
I can't, and so, uh--

1015
01:15:02,331 --> 01:15:05,232
Yeah, I better sit down.

1016
01:15:07,135 --> 01:15:10,400
Carry on, everybody, please.
Oh, one other thing.

1017
01:15:12,007 --> 01:15:15,238
Um, why don't we all...

1018
01:15:15,344 --> 01:15:18,279
have dinner again
tomorrow night, okay ?

1019
01:15:18,380 --> 01:15:20,314
Dinner again ?
Yeah.

1020
01:15:20,415 --> 01:15:23,213
You haven't had
enough of us yet, Dad ?

1021
01:15:24,953 --> 01:15:27,513
Mmm--

1022
01:15:27,623 --> 01:15:30,683
<i>mmm--</i>

1023
01:15:30,792 --> 01:15:32,692
no.

1024
01:15:35,998 --> 01:15:38,694
<i>Come here.</i>

1025
01:15:40,435 --> 01:15:42,995
- We'll be here.
- You bet we'll be here.

1026
01:15:43,105 --> 01:15:45,164
Bright-eyed
and bushy-tailed.

1027
01:15:48,510 --> 01:15:50,410
Joe.

1028
01:15:58,854 --> 01:16:01,118
Oh, no.

1029
01:16:01,223 --> 01:16:04,624
I would prefer
some peanut butter.

1030
01:16:04,726 --> 01:16:09,425
How would you like that,
sir ? On some kind
of toast ?
Toast.

1031
01:16:10,566 --> 01:16:14,434
No, just the butter.
Right away, sir.

1032
01:16:15,871 --> 01:16:18,601
Why do you like
peanut butter so much ?

1033
01:16:18,707 --> 01:16:20,641
I don't know.

1034
01:16:20,742 --> 01:16:23,472
Hmm. I adore
things like that.

1035
01:16:23,579 --> 01:16:26,707
Food I can't do without.
Don't you ?

1036
01:16:26,815 --> 01:16:28,715
Yes.

1037
01:16:28,817 --> 01:16:31,615
It comforts you,
doesn't it ?
Yes, I find
that it does.

1038
01:16:32,721 --> 01:16:35,212
Mind if I throw up ?
<i>[ Bill ]</i>
<i>Drew.</i>

1039
01:16:35,324 --> 01:16:37,519
Please.

1040
01:16:38,627 --> 01:16:40,788
[ Sighs ]

1041
01:16:42,264 --> 01:16:45,756
I'm very concerned
about the woman
you attended to today.

1042
01:16:45,867 --> 01:16:49,268
- I am too.
- <i>Has her pain abated?</i>

1043
01:16:49,371 --> 01:16:52,772
<i>We're doing what we can</i>
<i>for her, but, uh,</i>

1044
01:16:52,874 --> 01:16:55,274
it's not looking very good.

1045
01:16:55,377 --> 01:16:57,868
I'm sorry to hear that.
[ Whispers ]
Yeah.

1046
01:16:57,980 --> 01:17:00,073
Who are we talking about ?

1047
01:17:00,182 --> 01:17:03,379
But I know she's grateful
for the care you're giving her.

1048
01:17:03,485 --> 01:17:05,817
Is this a state secret ?

1049
01:17:05,921 --> 01:17:09,357
No, we're talking about
a patient of mine, 'cause...
<i>[ Drew ] Uh-huh.</i>

1050
01:17:09,458 --> 01:17:11,790
Joe stopped by
the hospital today.

1051
01:17:11,893 --> 01:17:15,761
<i>He did?</i>
<i>That's more than</i>
<i>we get to do.</i>

1052
01:17:15,864 --> 01:17:18,799
Maybe next time you go
to the hospital, you'll
take us along with you.

1053
01:17:18,900 --> 01:17:21,266
- Perhaps you could remind me.
- Well, I'll make a note of it.

1054
01:17:21,370 --> 01:17:24,134
- Anything else
I can do for you ?
- <i>I wanna come along too.</i>

1055
01:17:24,239 --> 01:17:26,469
See Susie strut her stuff.
<i>You're on, Quincie.</i>

1056
01:17:26,575 --> 01:17:31,410
Destination, hospital.
Joe, you can be
the tour guide, okay ?

1057
01:17:34,516 --> 01:17:37,314
Susan's a wonderful doctor.

1058
01:17:37,419 --> 01:17:39,944
I'm sure she is.

1059
01:17:44,159 --> 01:17:46,059
Bill ?
Yeah ?

1060
01:17:46,161 --> 01:17:48,061
I have to go.
It's been a hell
of a day.

1061
01:17:48,163 --> 01:17:51,223
I need a few minutes
to sort everything out.
See you tomorrow.

1062
01:17:57,139 --> 01:17:59,039
Joe ?

1063
01:18:02,744 --> 01:18:05,008
Yes, Bill ?

1064
01:18:05,113 --> 01:18:07,479
Um--

1065
01:18:07,582 --> 01:18:10,551
<i>::music:: [ Piano Note ]</i>

1066
01:18:13,922 --> 01:18:17,380
Why'd you go
to the hospital ?
I don't know.

1067
01:18:17,492 --> 01:18:21,019
You just curious ?
<i>::music:: [ Piano Note ]</i>
I guess.

1068
01:18:21,129 --> 01:18:23,927
About Susan ?
<i>::music:: [ Piano Note ]</i>

1069
01:18:24,032 --> 01:18:27,331
I wouldn't put it
that way.
How would you put it ?

1070
01:18:29,738 --> 01:18:33,538
You tell me, Bill.
No, how about
you telling me ?

1071
01:18:33,642 --> 01:18:36,133
I ask a simple question;
I expect a straight answer.

1072
01:18:36,244 --> 01:18:39,179
That's what I'm used to.
Anybody who doesn't
give it to me, I fire.

1073
01:18:40,515 --> 01:18:43,075
Are you going
to fire me, Bill ?

1074
01:18:46,822 --> 01:18:48,756
Drew ?

1075
01:18:49,858 --> 01:18:52,554
So, uh, I'll see you
tomorrow night ?

1076
01:18:52,661 --> 01:18:56,757
You include me out.
I've had enough
of the convocations.

1077
01:18:56,865 --> 01:19:01,199
You don't mean that.
You don't want
to disappoint Dad.

1078
01:19:01,303 --> 01:19:05,706
Daddy will do fine.
Besides, he's got Joe.
And it seems you do too.

1079
01:19:05,841 --> 01:19:09,242
You're out of line.
Well, that may be, but I don't
like the ubiquitous creep.

1080
01:19:09,344 --> 01:19:12,780
I don't like the way
he looks at you. I don't like
the way he talks to you.

1081
01:19:13,949 --> 01:19:16,247
And vice versa.

1082
01:19:20,021 --> 01:19:22,421
I'm sorry.

1083
01:19:24,760 --> 01:19:28,628
'Cause I like the way
he looks and talks to me.

1084
01:19:28,730 --> 01:19:31,130
And vice versa.

1085
01:19:33,668 --> 01:19:35,727
Okay ?

1086
01:19:37,172 --> 01:19:39,072
Not okay.

1087
01:19:40,642 --> 01:19:43,167
Thought we had
a good thing going here.

1088
01:19:43,278 --> 01:19:46,145
I thought
it was a good thing.

1089
01:19:47,415 --> 01:19:50,213
Well, that just goes to show
you never know.

1090
01:19:53,488 --> 01:19:55,547
Night.

1091
01:19:55,657 --> 01:19:58,592
[ Whispering ]
Good night.
<i>[ Door Closing ]</i>

1092
01:20:18,680 --> 01:20:21,581
How long have you
been standing there ?

1093
01:20:23,885 --> 01:20:26,911
I don't like the way
he spoke to you.

1094
01:20:27,055 --> 01:20:30,081
But I feel better now
because of the way
you spoke back.

1095
01:20:33,795 --> 01:20:37,458
Tell me
about yourself,Joe.

1096
01:20:37,566 --> 01:20:39,466
I mean, who are you ?

1097
01:20:39,568 --> 01:20:43,664
What are you doing here
with my father ?

1098
01:20:48,243 --> 01:20:50,177
You're not
going to tell me ?

1099
01:21:00,922 --> 01:21:03,413
You're married,
aren't you ?

1100
01:21:03,558 --> 01:21:06,721
Why ?

1101
01:21:06,828 --> 01:21:11,595
Because men
who never say anything
about themselves, they're--

1102
01:21:11,700 --> 01:21:14,260
they're always married.

1103
01:21:20,775 --> 01:21:24,677
So you're married ?
No, I'm not.

1104
01:21:26,615 --> 01:21:29,948
But you--
you have a girlfriend.

1105
01:21:30,051 --> 01:21:33,214
No.
[ Chuckles ]

1106
01:21:34,990 --> 01:21:38,653
Gay ?
No.

1107
01:21:46,234 --> 01:21:49,032
So, tell me,Joe--

1108
01:21:51,339 --> 01:21:55,571
How come a man
as attractive,
intelligent,

1109
01:21:55,677 --> 01:21:59,579
well-spoken...

1110
01:22:02,717 --> 01:22:07,586
diffident in the most
seductive way, and yet...

1111
01:22:10,558 --> 01:22:13,288
powerful...

1112
01:22:16,498 --> 01:22:19,365
is all alone
in this world ?

1113
01:22:33,048 --> 01:22:35,482
I'm sorry.

1114
01:22:37,018 --> 01:22:39,486
I'm s--
I didn't...

1115
01:22:39,621 --> 01:22:43,819
mean to pry, and, uh,

1116
01:22:43,925 --> 01:22:47,258
you obviously don't
want to tell me,

1117
01:22:47,362 --> 01:22:50,024
so we'll just--

1118
01:22:52,167 --> 01:22:54,931
We'll just
leave it a mystery.

1119
01:22:59,841 --> 01:23:03,743
That is the way you want it,
isn't it ?
Yes, thank you.

1120
01:23:16,591 --> 01:23:19,424
Where are you going ?

1121
01:23:19,527 --> 01:23:21,688
To bed.

1122
01:23:21,830 --> 01:23:24,856
- To bed ?
- Yes.

1123
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:27,434
I'm tired.

1124
01:23:33,208 --> 01:23:35,642
- <i>Good night, Daddy.</i>
- Good night.
Sleep well.

1125
01:23:35,744 --> 01:23:39,077
Okay.
See you tomorrow.
Good night. See you.

1126
01:23:39,180 --> 01:23:41,080
Good night, Susie.
Get some sleep.
Good night.

1127
01:23:41,182 --> 01:23:43,082
Yeah.
See you tomorrow.

1128
01:23:43,184 --> 01:23:45,209
Good night.
Good night.

1129
01:23:48,990 --> 01:23:51,891
That was wonderful.
Mmm.

1130
01:23:51,993 --> 01:23:54,928
It's good
to get together.
Mm-hmm.

1131
01:24:00,769 --> 01:24:03,829
Do you mind if I raise
a little caution flag ?

1132
01:24:03,972 --> 01:24:07,100
Raise away.

1133
01:24:07,242 --> 01:24:11,008
What is the nature
of your interest in Joe ?

1134
01:24:12,580 --> 01:24:15,378
Well--

1135
01:24:15,517 --> 01:24:18,918
Remember how you told me
about lightning striking ?

1136
01:24:19,054 --> 01:24:21,113
Mm-hmm.
[ Chuckles ]

1137
01:24:21,256 --> 01:24:25,249
The nature of it's
in there somewhere.

1138
01:24:25,393 --> 01:24:29,261
Yeah.
Well, I won't say you're
on the wrong track, but, uh--

1139
01:24:29,364 --> 01:24:31,764
Then what
will you say ?

1140
01:24:36,071 --> 01:24:40,007
I don't think
this is the lightning
you're looking for.

1141
01:24:40,141 --> 01:24:44,942
I mean, Drew is a good man.
I know I didn't seem to be
completely in his corner before,

1142
01:24:45,080 --> 01:24:47,605
but, uh, I've come
to appreciate that, um--

1143
01:24:47,749 --> 01:24:51,344
Now we love Drew ?
And Joe doesn't measure up ?

1144
01:24:51,486 --> 01:24:56,116
What's going on ?
Nothing.

1145
01:24:56,257 --> 01:24:59,192
When you say
''nothing'' that way,
it is not nothing.

1146
01:24:59,327 --> 01:25:01,591
Then what is it ?
It's something.

1147
01:25:01,729 --> 01:25:05,221
[ Breathes Deeply,
Chuckles ]

1148
01:25:06,468 --> 01:25:09,767
Okay.
Good night.

1149
01:25:09,904 --> 01:25:13,704
I'll see you tomorrow.
Yeah.
Good night.

1150
01:25:17,579 --> 01:25:19,479
[ Sighs ]

1151
01:25:20,115 --> 01:25:23,448
I know you're all
as uncomfortable as I am
to be meeting like this.

1152
01:25:23,585 --> 01:25:27,316
But I got a call last night
from John Bontecou.

1153
01:25:27,455 --> 01:25:32,085
Not only is he still interested,
he's sweetening his offer.

1154
01:25:34,229 --> 01:25:36,720
Although it pains me
to say it, in my opinion,

1155
01:25:36,865 --> 01:25:40,631
Bill Parrish dealt with us
preemptively...

1156
01:25:40,735 --> 01:25:43,295
in dismissing any deal
with Bontecou.

1157
01:25:43,438 --> 01:25:47,966
Therefore, I'm sorry to say
that if we're to examine
this new offer responsibly,

1158
01:25:48,109 --> 01:25:51,135
as the Board of Directors
of Parrish Communications,

1159
01:25:51,246 --> 01:25:55,706
we must do so
without its chairman.

1160
01:25:55,850 --> 01:25:58,250
There's one
additional element.

1161
01:25:58,386 --> 01:26:00,718
Bontecou is so anxious
to get us,

1162
01:26:00,855 --> 01:26:06,157
he said he'd take
Parrish Communications
with Bill Parrish or without.

1163
01:26:10,398 --> 01:26:12,298
[ Board Member Coughs ]

1164
01:26:14,269 --> 01:26:16,260
<i>In this crisis,</i>
<i>and be assured...</i>

1165
01:26:16,371 --> 01:26:20,000
this is a crisis,

1166
01:26:20,108 --> 01:26:22,167
it's not pleasant
to say the following.

1167
01:26:22,277 --> 01:26:25,576
But I would be remiss
if I did not.

1168
01:26:25,680 --> 01:26:28,672
When we present Bill
with the improved
Bontecou offer,

1169
01:26:28,783 --> 01:26:31,183
and if he still refuses
to let us consider it,

1170
01:26:31,286 --> 01:26:36,656
once more makes an adamant
or emotional rejection,
we will have no choice but to--

1171
01:26:36,758 --> 01:26:39,591
You're taking this
too far, Drew.

1172
01:26:41,196 --> 01:26:43,323
Am I not obligated to ?

1173
01:26:49,270 --> 01:26:52,000
[ Whispering ]
See if Quince is here.

1174
01:26:52,106 --> 01:26:55,371
[ Sighs ]
How did all this
come about ?

1175
01:26:55,476 --> 01:26:59,242
Crisis, Bill Parrish.
Crisis, his company.
Crisis for us.

1176
01:26:59,347 --> 01:27:03,010
It came about
with the arrival on the scene
of Mr.Joe Black.

1177
01:27:03,117 --> 01:27:07,213
Mr.Joe who ?
Joe Black.

1178
01:27:07,322 --> 01:27:10,189
He attends
our board meetings.

1179
01:27:10,291 --> 01:27:13,454
He sleeps at Bill's house.
He resides in his office.

1180
01:27:13,561 --> 01:27:15,586
He never leaves his side,
and, in my opinion,

1181
01:27:15,697 --> 01:27:18,097
is always in his ear,
telling Bill what to do.

1182
01:27:18,199 --> 01:27:20,360
And Bill is listening.

1183
01:27:20,468 --> 01:27:23,232
Who is Joe Black ?

1184
01:27:23,338 --> 01:27:25,806
What-- What is
his relationship
to Bill Parrish,

1185
01:27:25,907 --> 01:27:29,707
and most important,
what is behind his influence
on our chairman ?

1186
01:27:29,811 --> 01:27:35,249
<i>He's had advisors before.</i>
<i>Nobody tells Bill</i>
<i>what to do.</i>

1187
01:27:35,350 --> 01:27:38,717
<i>[ Footsteps Approaching ]</i>

1188
01:27:38,820 --> 01:27:43,689
Thanks for coming,
Quince.
Sure. Hi, Ed.

1189
01:27:43,791 --> 01:27:47,522
<i>Hi, folks.</i>

1190
01:27:47,629 --> 01:27:50,655
I didn't know everybody
was going to be here.

1191
01:27:50,765 --> 01:27:53,962
Nice surprise.

1192
01:27:54,068 --> 01:27:55,968
What's with
the new digs ?

1193
01:27:56,070 --> 01:28:00,564
<i>Drew's idea of cloak and dagger.</i>
<i>This is a secret meeting,</i>
<i>Quince.</i>

1194
01:28:00,675 --> 01:28:03,769
I hope you'll
respect its nature.

1195
01:28:13,021 --> 01:28:14,921
Have a seat, Quince.

1196
01:28:26,668 --> 01:28:28,602
[ Chuckles ]

1197
01:28:29,837 --> 01:28:33,136
Now, what we're trying
to do here is to, uh--

1198
01:28:33,241 --> 01:28:38,144
to gather our thoughts
in light of Bill's rejection
of Bontecou's offer...

1199
01:28:38,246 --> 01:28:40,578
and to make an appropriate
presentation to him...

1200
01:28:40,682 --> 01:28:44,049
as to how we think
the company might proceed.

1201
01:28:44,152 --> 01:28:47,952
Won't you share with our board
the information you gave me
last night ?

1202
01:28:50,925 --> 01:28:55,988
Well, uh, I'm hap--
I'm happy to tell you
I got good news.

1203
01:28:56,097 --> 01:28:59,157
As I was, uh,
as I was telling Drew,

1204
01:28:59,267 --> 01:29:03,966
uh, I've been
making a little hay while
the Bontecou sun was shining.

1205
01:29:04,072 --> 01:29:08,008
Two, possibly three,
new and boiling hot prospects
for merger.

1206
01:29:08,109 --> 01:29:11,237
Mm-hmm. And how did
Bill react to the leads
you've developed ?

1207
01:29:11,346 --> 01:29:16,875
He was interested.
Yeah, but he was concerned
about the timing ?

1208
01:29:16,984 --> 01:29:21,114
Timing ?
Yeah, he was concerned
about the timing ?

1209
01:29:21,222 --> 01:29:24,953
Yes.
He says it's up to Joe.

1210
01:29:28,129 --> 01:29:30,529
It's up to Joe.

1211
01:29:46,114 --> 01:29:48,708
::music:: Dum-da-dum ::music::
What's this ?

1212
01:29:48,816 --> 01:29:53,446
- Um, Annie made them.
- Who's Annie ?

1213
01:29:53,554 --> 01:29:56,352
Thank you, Lillian.
From La Rosette ?

1214
01:29:56,457 --> 01:29:59,756
She's only the most famous
pastry chef in America.

1215
01:29:59,861 --> 01:30:03,524
<i>Um, this is orange,</i>
<i>made with real Seville oranges.</i>

1216
01:30:03,631 --> 01:30:07,158
Oh.
<i>And, uh, that's lemon</i>
<i>on a mille-feuille crust.</i>

1217
01:30:07,268 --> 01:30:10,533
I don't like cake.

1218
01:30:10,638 --> 01:30:13,334
It's for the party, Dad.

1219
01:30:13,441 --> 01:30:16,877
Ah.
The goddamn party.

1220
01:30:16,978 --> 01:30:20,038
The goddamn party.
Mm-hmm.

1221
01:30:20,148 --> 01:30:22,639
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Did you hear that ?</i>
I'm sorry.

1222
01:30:23,985 --> 01:30:27,045
<i>The goddamn party.</i>
<i>Oh.</i>

1223
01:30:27,155 --> 01:30:29,817
<i>[ Bill ]</i>
<i>Come on, l--</i>
Here, let's try this one...

1224
01:30:29,924 --> 01:30:32,722
<i>right over here.</i>

1225
01:30:35,396 --> 01:30:38,229
Mmm.
[ Whimpers ]

1226
01:30:38,332 --> 01:30:42,792
This, this is terrific.
It has, um,

1227
01:30:42,904 --> 01:30:45,236
has vodka in it, Bill.

1228
01:30:45,339 --> 01:30:47,330
A little vodka, right ?
[ Crying, Gasping ]

1229
01:30:47,442 --> 01:30:49,410
Has, um, that fruity vodka,
that flavored stuff, right ?

1230
01:30:49,510 --> 01:30:53,241
Bill, put
your lips around this.
It's just out of this world.

1231
01:30:53,347 --> 01:30:57,374
<i>I'm sorry, honey.</i>
<i>You know, I'm no good</i>
<i>at this.</i>

1232
01:30:57,485 --> 01:30:59,385
Why don't you choose
whichever cake you'd like ?

1233
01:30:59,487 --> 01:31:02,513
<i>Hmm ?</i>
I knew you were
gonna say that.

1234
01:31:02,623 --> 01:31:05,091
What ?
<i>I mean</i>
<i>you just don't care.</i>

1235
01:31:05,193 --> 01:31:08,856
Oh, why am I doing this ?
I should have my head
examined again.

1236
01:31:08,963 --> 01:31:14,060
<i>Oh, my God.</i>
<i>I am trying to throw</i>
<i>the party of the century...</i>

1237
01:31:14,168 --> 01:31:16,864
[ Sobs ]
for my father in two days.

1238
01:31:16,971 --> 01:31:18,905
And you just don't
give a shit.
He gives a shit.

1239
01:31:19,006 --> 01:31:21,873
<i>He doesn't</i>
<i>give a shit!</i>
<i>He does.</i>

1240
01:31:21,976 --> 01:31:24,638
<i>[ Bill ] Allison.</i>
He does give a shit.
Don't you, Bill ?

1241
01:31:26,280 --> 01:31:29,272
Come on. Come on.

1242
01:31:31,919 --> 01:31:34,615
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>Smile.</i>
I'm sorry.

1243
01:31:39,393 --> 01:31:41,953
But what should we
tell Annie ?

1244
01:31:43,865 --> 01:31:45,765
::music:: Bum-bum-bum ::music::
[ Chuckles ]

1245
01:31:47,902 --> 01:31:51,838
This one.
Mmm.

1246
01:31:51,939 --> 01:31:55,466
- He gives a shit !
- <i>[ All Laughing ]</i>

1247
01:31:58,112 --> 01:32:00,672
Fantastic.

1248
01:32:02,216 --> 01:32:04,116
Thank you.

1249
01:32:11,392 --> 01:32:14,225
<i>[ Allison ]</i>
<i>Um, Mr. Black, would you</i>
<i>care for a piece ?</i>

1250
01:32:14,328 --> 01:32:16,762
Yes, I'd love one.

1251
01:32:23,137 --> 01:32:25,128
Have you had a chance
to, uh,

1252
01:32:25,239 --> 01:32:29,073
look at my father's
rare books ?

1253
01:32:29,176 --> 01:32:34,170
He has Jefferson's
parliamentary manual,
and, uh,

1254
01:32:34,282 --> 01:32:36,716
this first edition
of <i>Bleak House.</i>

1255
01:32:36,817 --> 01:32:39,547
I love your smell.

1256
01:32:44,959 --> 01:32:48,156
Well, I like
the way you smell too.

1257
01:32:56,370 --> 01:33:00,500
My mom always used to say
that you could set your heart
by that clock.

1258
01:33:06,781 --> 01:33:09,841
Could you ?

1259
01:33:09,951 --> 01:33:12,351
I never tried.

1260
01:33:15,156 --> 01:33:18,182
Till now.

1261
01:33:22,897 --> 01:33:25,422
Joe ?
Hmm ?

1262
01:33:28,869 --> 01:33:31,599
May I kiss you ?

1263
01:33:31,706 --> 01:33:34,675
Why, yes, you can.

1264
01:33:59,567 --> 01:34:01,967
Mmm.

1265
01:34:41,642 --> 01:34:43,974
Thank you.

1266
01:34:45,880 --> 01:34:48,644
You're welcome.

1267
01:34:53,087 --> 01:34:57,581
Joe ?
Mmm.

1268
01:34:57,692 --> 01:35:01,150
I don't know
who you are.

1269
01:35:04,932 --> 01:35:07,924
I'm Joe.
Mm-hmm.

1270
01:35:08,035 --> 01:35:11,835
And, uh,
you're Susan.

1271
01:35:11,939 --> 01:35:14,669
Mmm.

1272
01:35:14,775 --> 01:35:18,108
And...
I have this...

1273
01:35:18,212 --> 01:35:20,646
weak feeling
in my knees.

1274
01:35:20,748 --> 01:35:24,115
And is your heart
beating strangely ?
Yes.

1275
01:35:24,218 --> 01:35:26,186
Mm-hmm.
Faster.

1276
01:35:27,588 --> 01:35:30,455
The taste of your lips
and the touch
of your tongue--

1277
01:35:30,558 --> 01:35:32,651
that was wonderful.

1278
01:35:33,761 --> 01:35:35,661
Mmm.

1279
01:35:40,534 --> 01:35:42,434
I should, um...

1280
01:35:43,537 --> 01:35:45,437
I should go home.

1281
01:35:45,539 --> 01:35:48,474
Mmm.

1282
01:35:48,576 --> 01:35:51,044
Shouldn't I ?

1283
01:35:53,447 --> 01:35:55,813
Yeah.

1284
01:36:20,808 --> 01:36:24,574
Good night, Dad.
Good night.

1285
01:36:29,550 --> 01:36:32,280
Hello, Bill.

1286
01:36:34,789 --> 01:36:38,020
Hello.

1287
01:36:41,362 --> 01:36:44,991
Would you like to join me
and Allison and Quince
for a nightcap ?

1288
01:36:46,200 --> 01:36:50,500
No. Not right now.

1289
01:36:54,642 --> 01:36:56,906
Okay.

1290
01:36:59,613 --> 01:37:01,547
Then I'll say
good night.

1291
01:37:01,649 --> 01:37:03,549
Good night, Bill.

1292
01:37:07,354 --> 01:37:10,016
<i>[ Footsteps Departing ]</i>

1293
01:37:13,627 --> 01:37:16,027
Morning, Quince.
<i>Top of the morning, B.P.</i>

1294
01:37:16,130 --> 01:37:18,655
Hello, Quince.
Hey !

1295
01:37:21,402 --> 01:37:24,371
Hello,Jennifer.
Good morning,
Mr. Parrish.

1296
01:37:24,471 --> 01:37:26,701
The board
is waiting.
What ?

1297
01:37:26,807 --> 01:37:29,571
The board ?
Didn't you call
a board meeting ?

1298
01:37:29,677 --> 01:37:31,269
No.

1299
01:37:43,157 --> 01:37:45,921
- Good morning.
- Morning, Bill.

1300
01:37:46,026 --> 01:37:49,257
Did you want to have
a cup of coffee
or something, Bill ?

1301
01:37:51,899 --> 01:37:55,858
I don't think so.
Do you ?

1302
01:37:55,970 --> 01:38:01,033
To get to the point,
we've received new information
from John Bontecou...

1303
01:38:01,141 --> 01:38:03,871
concerning his desires
for this company
to merge with his.

1304
01:38:03,978 --> 01:38:06,606
<i>And we wanted</i>
<i>to set the details</i>
<i>before you.</i>

1305
01:38:06,714 --> 01:38:09,615
Is that it ?
<i>Bontecou wants</i>
<i>a quick response, and--</i>

1306
01:38:09,717 --> 01:38:12,584
The answer is no.
Quick enough
for you ?

1307
01:38:12,686 --> 01:38:15,052
- Don't you want to hear
the details ?
- <i>I'm not interested.</i>

1308
01:38:15,155 --> 01:38:18,386
<i>I'm not interested in</i>
<i>the big picture either.</i>
<i>What I am interested in...</i>

1309
01:38:18,492 --> 01:38:21,017
is how my board got convened
behind my back...

1310
01:38:21,128 --> 01:38:26,327
<i>and is entertaining a further</i>
<i>proposal from a man with whom</i>
<i>it offends me to do business.</i>

1311
01:38:26,433 --> 01:38:29,994
I made a decision.
Case closed.

1312
01:38:30,104 --> 01:38:32,971
So am I to understand
from your response...

1313
01:38:33,073 --> 01:38:35,837
that you do not want to
hear the details
of Bontecou's offer ?

1314
01:38:35,943 --> 01:38:37,843
Yes, you are
to understand that.

1315
01:38:37,945 --> 01:38:40,175
And now, may I ask
you a question ?

1316
01:38:40,281 --> 01:38:43,944
- <i>Certainly, Bill.</i>
- Are you running this board,
or am I ?

1317
01:38:48,622 --> 01:38:50,522
That's it ?

1318
01:38:52,526 --> 01:38:55,518
We've got a busy day ahead.
This meeting's already
set me behind.

1319
01:38:55,629 --> 01:38:59,656
Shall we adjourn ?
Uh, before we do, Bill,
while we're here--

1320
01:38:59,767 --> 01:39:02,258
There's a second question
the board would like
a response to.

1321
01:39:02,369 --> 01:39:06,240
Far simpler one.

1322
01:39:06,240 --> 01:39:09,038
Who is the man
standing to your left ?

1323
01:39:12,179 --> 01:39:14,909
I've already introduced
Mr. Black to you all.

1324
01:39:15,015 --> 01:39:17,882
<i>But who is he ?</i>
<i>What are his credentials ?</i>

1325
01:39:17,985 --> 01:39:20,545
What is his relationship
to you ?

1326
01:39:27,161 --> 01:39:30,096
The board
is deeply concerned.

1327
01:39:30,197 --> 01:39:33,633
We have reason to believe
Mr. Black is not only
influencing your decisions...

1328
01:39:33,734 --> 01:39:35,793
in regard to this company,

1329
01:39:35,903 --> 01:39:39,430
but that you are relying
on him to make them for you.

1330
01:39:43,744 --> 01:39:46,542
The lack of response, Bill,
is not appropriate.

1331
01:39:46,647 --> 01:39:49,115
We are your board.

1332
01:39:49,216 --> 01:39:52,549
We have a right
to know how you are managing
the operations of this company.

1333
01:39:52,653 --> 01:39:57,283
<i>And, most importantly,</i>
<i>that you have not delegated</i>
<i>someone to do it for you.</i>

1334
01:39:57,391 --> 01:39:59,325
<i>Okay ?</i>

1335
01:40:00,627 --> 01:40:03,755
One more time.
Who is Joe Black ?

1336
01:40:15,009 --> 01:40:17,842
A motion has been brought
before the board...

1337
01:40:17,945 --> 01:40:20,846
to invoke Article 1 9
of the corporate charter.

1338
01:40:20,948 --> 01:40:23,178
In English, please.

1339
01:40:23,283 --> 01:40:25,945
[ Sighs ]

1340
01:40:27,554 --> 01:40:32,253
Mandatory retirement
on our chairman's 65th birthday,

1341
01:40:32,359 --> 01:40:35,123
<i>at which time the chairman</i>
<i>will be named emeritus.</i>

1342
01:40:35,229 --> 01:40:38,198
<i>You're welcome to attend</i>
<i>all meetings...</i>

1343
01:40:38,298 --> 01:40:41,267
<i>and will serve as</i>
<i>international spokesman</i>
<i>for the corporation.</i>

1344
01:40:41,368 --> 01:40:43,666
Plus, of course,
a settlement,

1345
01:40:43,771 --> 01:40:47,502
a golden parachute
of such magnitude that his feet
will never touch the ground.

1346
01:40:49,610 --> 01:40:53,046
Please indicate your vote
by a yes or no.

1347
01:40:53,180 --> 01:40:56,343
- Yes.
- Yes.
- Yes.

1348
01:40:56,450 --> 01:40:59,510
[ Several Members At Once ]
Yes.

1349
01:40:59,620 --> 01:41:02,783
<i>[ Affirmations Continue ]</i>

1350
01:41:02,890 --> 01:41:06,883
- No.
- No.

1351
01:41:08,562 --> 01:41:10,996
Motion's passed.

1352
01:41:14,902 --> 01:41:18,303
We will, of course, delay
the announcement out of respect
for our former chairman...

1353
01:41:18,405 --> 01:41:23,069
<i>until after the celebration</i>
<i>of his birthday this weekend.</i>

1354
01:41:23,177 --> 01:41:26,772
Well, thanks for allowing me
to save face, Drew.

1355
01:41:26,880 --> 01:41:29,747
<i>The other motion before us</i>
<i>is the acceptance</i>
<i>ofJohn Bontecou's offer...</i>

1356
01:41:29,850 --> 01:41:33,946
to merge this corporation
with Bontecou International.

1357
01:41:50,070 --> 01:41:53,233
Okay.
Joe ?

1358
01:42:04,017 --> 01:42:06,144
Who I am...

1359
01:42:06,253 --> 01:42:10,155
and what my relationship is
to William Parrish...

1360
01:42:10,290 --> 01:42:13,521
will be divulged
in our own good time.

1361
01:42:14,761 --> 01:42:19,130
Okay.
Thank you, Mr. Black.

1362
01:42:23,837 --> 01:42:25,828
It's not over
till it's over.

1363
01:42:25,973 --> 01:42:28,237
Please, Eddie,
no ''fat lady sings'' stuff.

1364
01:42:28,342 --> 01:42:32,676
I still sense some doubt
in this group.
We could turn it around.

1365
01:42:32,779 --> 01:42:34,747
You'll be up
in the country ?
Yeah.

1366
01:42:34,882 --> 01:42:37,908
The big celebration
of my mandatory
retirement birthday.

1367
01:42:38,051 --> 01:42:39,951
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>
You're an honored guest,
Eddie.

1368
01:42:40,053 --> 01:42:43,216
I'm gonna
stick it out here.
We still have a shot.

1369
01:42:43,323 --> 01:42:46,884
Get John's office on the phone.
Tell them I'll be there
in 20 minutes.

1370
