We should think about
getting started, Bill.

1836
02:29:20,785 --> 02:29:22,685
Mm-hmm.

1837
02:29:29,093 --> 02:29:31,721
It'll just be us.

1838
02:29:35,599 --> 02:29:37,533
Thank you.

1839
02:29:43,975 --> 02:29:46,034
[ Knocking ]
Bill ?

1840
02:29:47,945 --> 02:29:50,539
Come in.

1841
02:29:52,183 --> 02:29:55,619
I got him. The helicopter
will be here in two minutes.

1842
02:29:55,753 --> 02:29:58,620
How are we on time ?

1843
02:29:58,723 --> 02:30:01,214
Okay.

1844
02:30:01,359 --> 02:30:03,020
Get him in here.

1845
02:30:03,160 --> 02:30:06,561
[ Beeps ]
May ?

1846
02:30:06,664 --> 02:30:08,723
Yes, sir ?
I know you're busy,

1847
02:30:08,866 --> 02:30:11,096
but I want you to put in a call
to Eddie Sloane for me.

1848
02:30:11,235 --> 02:30:13,669
At home, sir ?
No, he's at the office.

1849
02:30:14,138 --> 02:30:17,198
This is damn big
of Bill.

1850
02:30:17,341 --> 02:30:19,309
Ooh. You all right ?
Yeah.

1851
02:30:19,443 --> 02:30:21,468
Also smart, you know ?

1852
02:30:21,612 --> 02:30:25,207
Well, he had no choice.
He knows you're
a formidable adversary.

1853
02:30:25,349 --> 02:30:28,648
He said that ?
Yeah, I mean, you got him
by the short hairs.

1854
02:30:28,786 --> 02:30:30,754
Yeah, the short
and gray hairs.

1855
02:30:30,888 --> 02:30:33,652
We're all here, Bill.
<i>I appreciate this, Eddie.</i>

1856
02:30:33,791 --> 02:30:38,751
Members of the board, this will
just take a minute of your time.

1857
02:30:38,896 --> 02:30:43,492
As custodians of the company,
you may receive information
from what follows...

1858
02:30:43,634 --> 02:30:48,162
that will be valuable
to you or not.

1859
02:30:48,305 --> 02:30:50,739
Either way, thanks.
We're all ears.

1860
02:30:50,875 --> 02:30:52,274
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>
Thanks.

1861
02:30:55,046 --> 02:30:56,946
Good evening, Bill.

1862
02:30:57,048 --> 02:30:59,278
Thank you, Quince.

1863
02:30:59,417 --> 02:31:04,855
I just wanted to say how
appreciative I am of this,
um, grand gesture.

1864
02:31:04,989 --> 02:31:06,684
Shut up and sit down.

1865
02:31:12,830 --> 02:31:15,230
<i>You're a useless sack</i>
<i>of shit, Drew.</i>

1866
02:31:15,332 --> 02:31:17,266
You played footsie
with John Bontecou...

1867
02:31:17,401 --> 02:31:19,835
so you could
dismember my company
to line your own pockets.

1868
02:31:19,937 --> 02:31:22,929
I don't know where you get
that idea. The board agreed--

1869
02:31:23,074 --> 02:31:27,101
The board didn't know you were
a mole who burrowed inside
so you could bury us all.

1870
02:31:27,244 --> 02:31:30,475
Is this Mr. Black's fantasy ?
Another one of his whoppers ?

1871
02:31:30,614 --> 02:31:33,742
Aren't you sick of
this asshole lurking around ?
Nobody knows who he is.

1872
02:31:33,884 --> 02:31:35,818
But one thing
everybody does know,

1873
02:31:35,920 --> 02:31:39,481
he somehow got your ear
and has been pouring poison
into it ever since.

1874
02:31:39,623 --> 02:31:42,751
You're the poison, Drew.

1875
02:31:42,893 --> 02:31:45,726
You've operated behind
the scenes to suborn
the trust of a man...

1876
02:31:45,863 --> 02:31:49,560
who has stamped you
with his imprimatur of
class, elegance and stature.

1877
02:31:49,700 --> 02:31:54,296
<i>I've had the opportunity</i>
<i>to be witness to every kind</i>
<i>and degree of deception.</i>

1878
02:31:54,405 --> 02:31:58,000
But Bill Parrish has been
on the receiving end of
machinations so Machiavellian...

1879
02:31:58,142 --> 02:32:00,337
that it has rarely been
my experience to encounter.

1880
02:32:00,478 --> 02:32:06,007
And yet, he has combatted them
stoically and selflessly,
without revealing my identity.

1881
02:32:06,117 --> 02:32:09,177
Had he violated
the vow of secrecy he took,

1882
02:32:09,320 --> 02:32:11,811
<i>his task would</i>
<i>have been far easier.</i>

1883
02:32:11,956 --> 02:32:14,823
<i>He could have turned</i>
<i>defeat into victory.</i>

1884
02:32:14,959 --> 02:32:17,826
But he is too honorable a man
to have done that.

1885
02:32:17,928 --> 02:32:23,230
Because of me,
he has lost his work,
his company, his reputation.

1886
02:32:23,334 --> 02:32:27,293
So now,
given these losses,

1887
02:32:27,438 --> 02:32:31,841
I'm compelled to end
the need for secrecy.

1888
02:32:33,511 --> 02:32:36,002
The time has come
to tell you who I am.

1889
02:32:41,685 --> 02:32:44,620
So tell me. Tell me.
I'm peeing in my pants.

1890
02:32:44,722 --> 02:32:47,555
- And you're going
to pee some more.
-Joe, don't do this.

1891
02:32:47,658 --> 02:32:50,286
It's okay, Bill. It's time
we put this person in his place.

1892
02:32:50,394 --> 02:32:53,090
<i>It's not necessary, Joe.</i>
<i>Drew's gonna step aside.</i>

1893
02:32:53,197 --> 02:32:56,223
- I'm not stepping anywhere.
- I appreciate your
gentlemanliness.

1894
02:32:56,367 --> 02:32:58,460
But what we need to do here
is drive the dagger home.

1895
02:32:58,569 --> 02:33:00,901
- ''The dagger'' ?
- I told you to shut up !

1896
02:33:01,005 --> 02:33:03,473
Prepare yourself, Drew.

1897
02:33:03,574 --> 02:33:06,065
I--
<i>Joe, please.</i>

1898
02:33:06,177 --> 02:33:07,974
Kindly let me
take it from here.

1899
02:33:08,078 --> 02:33:09,773
Am--
<i>Don't.</i>

1900
02:33:14,652 --> 02:33:17,815
An agent for the
Internal Revenue Service.

1901
02:33:25,596 --> 02:33:26,563
Bill ?
Huh ?

1902
02:33:26,664 --> 02:33:28,325
Bill.

1903
02:33:32,102 --> 02:33:33,501
Bill.
Yeah.

1904
02:33:33,604 --> 02:33:37,233
[ Clears Throat ]
Yes, he's, um--

1905
02:33:37,341 --> 02:33:40,538
He's an agent for the
Internal Revenue Service.

1906
02:33:40,644 --> 02:33:43,477
Mmm, yes, we were convinced
that Bontecou, on past deals,

1907
02:33:43,581 --> 02:33:45,549
has structured his mergers
and acquisitions...

1908
02:33:45,649 --> 02:33:49,813
in suspicious and complicated
ways so as to evade paying
the taxes he is liable for.

1909
02:33:49,920 --> 02:33:54,857
<i>The agency asked Bill for</i>
<i>his cooperation in an undercover</i>
<i>investigation of Bontecou.</i>

1910
02:33:54,959 --> 02:34:00,829
We wanted to go after him,
and this deal gave us
that perfect opportunity.

1911
02:34:00,931 --> 02:34:05,334
And I offered
to cooperate.
And we're very grateful.

1912
02:34:05,436 --> 02:34:10,032
Uh, Agent Joe Black here--
Of course, that's not
his real name--

1913
02:34:10,140 --> 02:34:12,108
smelled out
your involvement, Drew.

1914
02:34:12,209 --> 02:34:16,305
<i>He developed evidence you were</i>
<i>working both sides of the fence.</i>

1915
02:34:16,413 --> 02:34:20,713
Unfortunately,
that is what is known
as a conflict of interest.

1916
02:34:20,818 --> 02:34:22,786
Undisclosed
conflict of interest.

1917
02:34:22,886 --> 02:34:25,047
An offense.
An indictable offense.

1918
02:34:25,155 --> 02:34:28,454
And a likely
conviction.
Very likely.

1919
02:34:28,559 --> 02:34:31,460
I think I'd like
to talk to my lawyer.

1920
02:34:31,562 --> 02:34:36,022
No lawyers, Drew.
Uh, we're gonna
offer you a deal.

1921
02:34:36,133 --> 02:34:39,728
Confess to the board every
detail of your participation,
then submit your resignation.

1922
02:34:39,837 --> 02:34:41,464
What do I get ?

1923
02:34:41,572 --> 02:34:43,199
You get not to go to jail.

1924
02:34:43,307 --> 02:34:45,366
You're talking
through your hat.

1925
02:34:45,476 --> 02:34:47,967
You're offering me a deal
because you've got no proof.

1926
02:34:48,078 --> 02:34:52,139
Proof? We've got
plenty of proof.
He's talking through his lips.

1927
02:34:52,249 --> 02:34:56,242
Drew, make no mistake.
Should you choose to test
my resolve in this matter,

1928
02:34:56,353 --> 02:34:59,083
you will be looking
at an outcome that
will have a finality...

1929
02:34:59,189 --> 02:35:01,453
that is beyond
your comprehension.

1930
02:35:01,558 --> 02:35:05,494
And you will not be counting
the days or the months
or the years,

1931
02:35:05,596 --> 02:35:08,861
but millenniums
in a place with no doors.

1932
02:35:11,835 --> 02:35:14,235
All right, you win.

1933
02:35:14,338 --> 02:35:16,670
Soon as I get back to the city,
I'll meet with the board.

1934
02:35:16,774 --> 02:35:19,868
<i>[ Eddie ] You're meeting</i>
<i>with the board right now,</i>
<i>Drew. Resignation accepted.</i>

1935
02:35:19,977 --> 02:35:24,243
Moreover, I propose
a motion to reconfirm
William Parrish...

1936
02:35:24,348 --> 02:35:27,408
as chairman of the board
of Parrish Communications,

1937
02:35:27,518 --> 02:35:31,215
<i>as well as</i>
<i>a rejection of the merger</i>
<i>with Bontecou International.</i>

1938
02:35:31,322 --> 02:35:34,621
<i>How say you, board?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

1939
02:35:34,725 --> 02:35:36,989
<i>- Yes.</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>
<i>The motion is passed.</i>

1940
02:35:37,094 --> 02:35:39,187
<i>[ Bill ]</i>
<i>Thank you.</i>
<i>That's great.</i>

1941
02:35:39,296 --> 02:35:43,062
But it's more than
I bargained for. I just wanted
to set the record straight.

1942
02:35:43,167 --> 02:35:47,365
<i>You have. Sounds like</i>
<i>these guys want you back, Bill.</i>
<i>We'll get their apologies later.</i>

1943
02:35:47,471 --> 02:35:51,305
<i>Meanwhile, enjoy your party.</i>
<i>Celebrate. I'll attend</i>
<i>to the nasty details.</i>

1944
02:35:51,408 --> 02:35:53,876
And, Mr. Black,
may we say thank you ?

1945
02:35:53,977 --> 02:35:57,037
My pleasure.
This is an I.R.S. agent's dream.

1946
02:35:57,147 --> 02:35:59,274
I'll be promoted
chief of section off this.

1947
02:35:59,383 --> 02:36:01,817
[ Clicks ]

1948
02:36:06,023 --> 02:36:09,049
Who would have believed it ?

1949
02:36:09,159 --> 02:36:11,286
You an I.R.S. agent ?

1950
02:36:13,931 --> 02:36:16,991
Death and taxes.

1951
02:36:20,971 --> 02:36:25,101
<i>::music:: [ Ends ]</i>
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

1952
02:36:25,209 --> 02:36:28,736
<i>::music:: [ ''Happy Birthday'']</i>
::music:: Happy birthday to you ::music::

1953
02:36:28,846 --> 02:36:32,145
::music:: Happy birthday to you ::music::

1954
02:36:32,249 --> 02:36:37,744
::music:: Happy birthday
dear William ::music::

1955
02:36:37,855 --> 02:36:43,487
::music:: Happy birthday to you ::music::::music::

1956
02:37:23,400 --> 02:37:25,664
[ Cheering ]

1957
02:37:25,769 --> 02:37:28,738
Speech ! Speech !
Speech !

1958
02:37:28,839 --> 02:37:33,674
[ Chanting ]
Speech ! Speech ! Speech !

1959
02:37:33,777 --> 02:37:36,143
Thank you.

1960
02:37:36,246 --> 02:37:38,441
[ Sighs ]

1961
02:37:38,549 --> 02:37:43,509
I thought I was gonna
sneak away tonight.
[ Crowd ] No !

1962
02:37:43,620 --> 02:37:45,520
[ Scattered Laughing ]

1963
02:37:45,622 --> 02:37:48,648
What a glorious night.

1964
02:37:48,759 --> 02:37:51,159
Every face I see
is a memory.

1965
02:37:51,261 --> 02:37:56,198
It may not be a perfectly
perfect memory.

1966
02:37:56,300 --> 02:38:01,761
Uh, sometimes we had
our ups and downs.

1967
02:38:01,872 --> 02:38:04,204
But we're all together,

1968
02:38:04,308 --> 02:38:07,607
and you're mine for a night.

1969
02:38:10,581 --> 02:38:16,383
And I'm gonna break
precedent and tell you
my one candle wish.

1970
02:38:16,487 --> 02:38:19,615
That you would have a life
as lucky as mine,

1971
02:38:19,723 --> 02:38:24,717
<i>where you can wake up</i>
<i>one morning and say,</i>

1972
02:38:24,828 --> 02:38:27,820
''I don't want anything more.''

1973
02:38:37,007 --> 02:38:40,875
Sixty-five years.

1974
02:38:40,978 --> 02:38:44,470
Don't they
go by in a blink ?

1975
02:38:54,057 --> 02:38:56,685
<i>::music:: [ Resumes ]</i>

1976
02:39:27,491 --> 02:39:29,459
Hi.

1977
02:39:29,560 --> 02:39:33,087
Oh. What a night.

1978
02:39:33,196 --> 02:39:36,791
I'm having
a hell of a time.

1979
02:39:39,603 --> 02:39:43,334
You were right...
about Joe.

1980
02:39:43,440 --> 02:39:46,204
He, uh--

1981
02:39:46,310 --> 02:39:48,210
He is going somewhere.

1982
02:39:50,080 --> 02:39:52,048
I'm sorry.

1983
02:39:54,418 --> 02:39:56,613
You relieved ?

1984
02:39:57,721 --> 02:40:00,815
Yes, but--

1985
02:40:00,924 --> 02:40:03,392
[ Sighs ]
But what ?

1986
02:40:09,666 --> 02:40:12,362
I want you to know
how much I love you,

1987
02:40:12,469 --> 02:40:15,734
that you've given a meaning
to my life that I had
no right to expect,

1988
02:40:15,839 --> 02:40:18,307
that no one can
ever take from me.

1989
02:40:18,408 --> 02:40:20,501
Dad--
No !

1990
02:40:20,611 --> 02:40:24,638
I love you so much.

1991
02:40:24,748 --> 02:40:27,649
And I want you
to promise me something.

1992
02:40:27,751 --> 02:40:32,245
I don't want you
to ever worry about me.

1993
02:40:32,356 --> 02:40:35,814
And if anything
should happen,
I'm gonna be okay.

1994
02:40:35,926 --> 02:40:38,827
And everything's
gonna be all right.

1995
02:40:38,929 --> 02:40:40,829
And I have no regrets.

1996
02:40:40,931 --> 02:40:44,230
And I want you
to feel the same way.

1997
02:40:50,040 --> 02:40:51,940
I love you, Daddy.

1998
02:40:52,042 --> 02:40:54,772
That's why it's okay.

1999
02:41:00,150 --> 02:41:02,050
No regrets ?

2000
02:41:03,887 --> 02:41:05,912
No regrets.

2001
02:41:06,023 --> 02:41:08,218
That's a good feeling,
isn't it ?

2002
02:41:08,325 --> 02:41:10,987
Yeah.

2003
02:41:15,065 --> 02:41:17,260
Everybody's saying good-bye.

2004
02:41:20,237 --> 02:41:22,637
I'm still here.

2005
02:41:24,541 --> 02:41:26,975
Would you like to dance
with me, Susan ?

2006
02:41:29,980 --> 02:41:32,175
Yeah.

2007
02:41:37,454 --> 02:41:40,082
If you don't mind
dancing with an old fogey
like me.

2008
02:41:40,190 --> 02:41:45,355
Oh, Dad, you're not old.

2009
02:41:49,733 --> 02:41:52,327
You'll never be old.

2010
02:41:57,074 --> 02:41:58,974
Can I get you
anything, sir ?

2011
02:41:59,076 --> 02:42:02,170
No.

2012
02:42:02,279 --> 02:42:04,747
Do you have
any peanut butter ?

2013
02:42:06,149 --> 02:42:08,310
Uh, I don't think so, sir.

2014
02:42:08,418 --> 02:42:13,117
Mmm. Thank you anyway.

2015
02:42:13,223 --> 02:42:15,691
You're welcome.

2016
02:43:54,658 --> 02:43:56,956
What's that ?

2017
02:43:57,060 --> 02:43:59,551
[ Chuckles ]
The fireworks are starting.

2018
02:43:59,663 --> 02:44:02,826
Let's go down and watch.

2019
02:44:02,933 --> 02:44:06,596
<i>[ Fireworks Popping ]</i>

2020
02:44:06,703 --> 02:44:10,639
Shall we ?
You go on ahead, honey.

2021
02:44:10,740 --> 02:44:13,265
I'm just gonna
catch my breath.

2022
02:44:21,484 --> 02:44:23,384
[ Whispers ]
Okay.

2023
02:44:41,805 --> 02:44:43,705
Okay.

2024
02:45:57,414 --> 02:45:59,882
Happy birthday, Bill.

2025
02:45:59,983 --> 02:46:01,883
Thank you.

2026
02:46:04,688 --> 02:46:07,088
Did you say good-bye ?

2027
02:46:07,190 --> 02:46:10,091
Not exactly.

2028
02:46:10,260 --> 02:46:13,718
I guess you have
your reasons.

2029
02:46:13,830 --> 02:46:15,730
Yes.

2030
02:46:15,832 --> 02:46:19,359
<i>[ Popping Continues ]</i>

2031
02:46:21,972 --> 02:46:24,497
Now that we have a moment,

2032
02:46:24,607 --> 02:46:28,566
would you mind
if I expressed my gratitude
for what you did for Susan ?

2033
02:46:31,381 --> 02:46:36,045
I've never heard
her speak of any man
as she spoke of you.

2034
02:46:36,152 --> 02:46:39,144
That's what I always
wanted for her.

2035
02:46:41,524 --> 02:46:44,391
But what happens
to her now ?

2036
02:46:45,695 --> 02:46:48,391
I wouldn't worry
about it, Bill.

2037
02:46:48,498 --> 02:46:51,399
These things have a way
of working out.

2038
02:46:54,838 --> 02:46:58,706
Would you mind if
I expressed my gratitude ?

2039
02:47:00,110 --> 02:47:02,806
For you,

2040
02:47:02,912 --> 02:47:05,506
for the time
you've given me,

2041
02:47:05,615 --> 02:47:07,776
for the person you are.

2042
02:47:10,420 --> 02:47:15,050
Don't blow smoke up my ass.
You'll ruin my autopsy.

2043
02:47:26,169 --> 02:47:28,729
It's hard to let go,
isn't it ?

2044
02:47:32,675 --> 02:47:34,609
Yes, it is, Bill.

2045
02:47:36,780 --> 02:47:39,840
Well, that's life.

2046
02:47:39,949 --> 02:47:42,417
What can I tell you ?

2047
02:48:16,853 --> 02:48:18,787
Should I be afraid ?

2048
02:48:20,824 --> 02:48:22,951
Not a man like you.

2049
02:49:54,651 --> 02:49:56,551
You're here.

2050
02:50:01,191 --> 02:50:03,125
You bet.

2051
02:50:06,396 --> 02:50:08,830
Well, where did you go ?

2052
02:50:10,300 --> 02:50:13,667
I don't know.

2053
02:50:13,770 --> 02:50:15,670
I don't--

2054
02:50:20,610 --> 02:50:24,671
I-- I don't know,
you know. I--

2055
02:50:26,549 --> 02:50:31,316
It's all kind of blurred up
and hazy, but--

2056
02:50:31,421 --> 02:50:36,358
Would you know what I mean
if I said I don't think
I'll ever figure it out ?

2057
02:50:40,363 --> 02:50:42,490
But now I'm back.

2058
02:50:47,670 --> 02:50:49,535
That's it ?

2059
02:50:53,876 --> 02:50:57,607
Well, I don't know
what else to say. Looks
like a hell of a party.

2060
02:51:00,583 --> 02:51:03,017
You think so ?

2061
02:51:05,521 --> 02:51:08,422
You look beautiful.

2062
02:51:09,759 --> 02:51:12,193
When you disappeared
around the corner,

2063
02:51:12,295 --> 02:51:17,198
I wasn't sure if I was
ever gonna see you again.

2064
02:51:28,177 --> 02:51:30,111
Hey, are you all right ?

2065
02:51:39,022 --> 02:51:42,753
The coffee shop.
Yep.

2066
02:51:42,859 --> 02:51:47,592
I asked you if I said
something wrong and you said no,
